Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.50,0:00:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn华文楷体\fs20\1c&H3CF1F3&\b0}字幕来源：YYeTs字幕组   后期处理：不死别姬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.84,0:00:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn华文楷体\fs44\fad(200,600)\bord2\pos(188.6,232.9)\c&HF6F6F6&\1a&H00&}肖申克的救赎
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.82,0:02:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,杜弗伦先生  请你\N{\rEng}Mr. Dufresne, describe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.99,0:02:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,描述一下命案当晚你和妻子争吵的情形\N{\rEng}the confrontation you had with your wife the night she was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.79,0:02:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn华文楷体\fs26\fad(400,400)\pos(271.6,219)\bord2}马克·洛斯顿
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.00,0:02:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我们吵的很凶\N{\rEng}It was very bitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.00,0:02:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,她说不怕我知道  她讨厌偷偷摸摸\N{\rEng}She said she was glad I knew,that she hated all the sneaking around.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.87,0:02:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,她还说  想去雷诺市办离婚\N{\rEng}And she said that she wanted a divorce in Reno.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.61,0:02:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-你怎样回答   -我拒绝离婚\N{\rEng}-What was your response?  -I told her I would not grant one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.48,0:02:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"你别想活着去雷诺市"\N{\rEng}"I'll see you in hell before I see you in Reno."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.85,0:02:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,邻居作证你说过这句话\N{\rEng}Those were your words, according to your neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.25,0:02:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,也许吧\N{\rEng}If they say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我气炸了  记不清楚\N{\rEng}I really don't remember. I was upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.19,0:02:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你们吵完以后呢\N{\rEng}What happened after you argued with your wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.79,0:02:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,她收拾行李\N{\rEng}She packed a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,去跟昆丁先生住一起\N{\rEng}She packed a bag to go and stay with Mr. Quentin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.53,0:02:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,葛兰·昆丁  乡村俱乐部的高球教练\N{\rEng}Glenn Quentin, golf pro at the Snowden Hills Country Club
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.84,0:03:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你最近才发现  他是你太太的情夫\N{\rEng}whom you had discovered was your wife's lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.28,0:03:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你跟踪她吗\N{\rEng}Did you follow her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.81,0:03:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我先去酒吧买醉\N{\rEng}I went to a few bars first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,然后去他家  但没人在\N{\rEng}Later, I drove to his house to confront them. They weren't home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.05,0:03:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我停了车\N{\rEng}I parked in the turnout
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.35,0:03:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,等他们\N{\rEng}and waited.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.49,0:03:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,用意何在\N{\rEng}With what intention?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.76,0:03:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我不确定\N{\rEng}I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.33,0:03:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我醉了\N{\rEng}I was confused
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,糊里糊涂\N{\rEng}drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.77,0:03:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我想\N{\rEng}I think
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.17,0:03:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,最多只是吓吓他们\N{\rEng}mostly I wanted to scare them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.40,0:03:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,结果他们一回来  你就冲进屋杀了他们\N{\rEng}When they arrived, you went up to the house and murdered them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.97,0:03:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我酒逐渐醒了\N{\rEng}No, I was sobering up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.31,0:03:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,开车回家睡觉\N{\rEng}I got back in the car and I drove home to sleep it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.18,0:03:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,回家途中  把枪丢进了皇家河\N{\rEng}Along the way, I threw my gun into the Royal River.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.35,0:03:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经讲的很清楚了\N{\rEng}I've been very clear on this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.59,0:03:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但清洁工第二天早晨上工时\N{\rEng}I get hazy where the cleaning woman shows up the following morning
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.86,0:03:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,发现了床上的两具尸体\N{\rEng}and finds your wife in bed with her lover
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.66,0:03:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,身上全是38毫米的弹孔\N{\rEng}riddled with.38-caliber bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:04:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你不觉得这很巧吗   还是只有我这么想\N{\rEng}Does that strike you as a fantastic coincidence, or is it just me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.23,0:04:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,是  很巧\N{\rEng}Yes, it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.44,0:04:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但你仍声称早在案发之前\N{\rEng}Yet you still maintain you threw your gun into the river
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,就已经丢掉了枪\N{\rEng}before the murders took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.07,0:04:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,这种说法很省事\N{\rEng}That's very convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.51,0:04:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这是实话\N{\rEng}It's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.55,0:04:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,警方打捞了三天都没找到\N{\rEng}The police dragged that river for three days, and nary a gun was found
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.28,0:04:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这样就无法比对\N{\rEng}so no comparison could be made
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.09,0:04:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你的手枪和\N{\rEng}between your gun and the bullets
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.69,0:04:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,受害者尸体上的弹痕\N{\rEng}taken from the bloodstained corpses of the victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.73,0:04:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,所以呢\N{\rEng}And that also
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.59,0:04:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这样很省事  不是吗  杜弗伦先生\N{\rEng}is very convenient. Isn't it, Mr. Dufresne?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.37,0:04:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我是清白的\N{\rEng}Since I am innocent of this crime
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.64,0:04:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,所以找不到枪反而很费事\N{\rEng}I find it decidedly inconvenient that the gun was never found.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.16,0:05:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们  一切证据都向各位报告了\N{\rEng}Ladies and gentlemen, you've heard all the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,脚印和胎痕证明  被告在场\N{\rEng}We have the accused at the scene of the crime. We have footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.77,0:05:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,散落在地面的子弹上有他的指纹\N{\rEng}Bullets on the ground bearing his fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.84,0:05:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,酒瓶碎片上同样也有指痕\N{\rEng}A broken bourbon bottle, likewise with fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,最重要的是\N{\rEng}And most of all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.77,0:05:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,一位美女与情夫\N{\rEng}we have a beautiful young woman and her lover
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.04,0:05:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,相拥而死\N{\rEng}lying dead in each other's arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.25,0:05:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,他们是有伤风化\N{\rEng}They had sinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,但是  他们真的\N{\rEng}But was their crime so great
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.89,0:05:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,罪该致死吗\N{\rEng}as to merit a death sentence?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.29,0:05:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,与此同时请各位\N{\rEng}While you think about that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.03,0:05:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,再考虑一件事\N{\rEng}think about this:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.70,0:05:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}左轮枪只能装六发子弹  而非八发\N{\rEng}A revolver holds six bullets, not eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.85,0:05:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn华文楷体\fs18\fad(400,400)\pos(200.5,170.3)\c&HEFFCFF&\1a&H00&\bord1\shad1}改编自\N{\fs20}史蒂芬金的短篇小说\N《丽塔·海华丝及肖申克监狱的赎罪》
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.08,0:05:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}所以他并非一时冲动\N{\rEng}I submit that this was not a hot-blooded crime of passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.54,0:05:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}冲动并不可宽恕  但可理解\N{\rEng}That at least could be understood, if not condoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.54,0:05:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,然而\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.77,0:05:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,这是复仇\N{\rEng}This was revenge
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.11,0:05:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,残忍而冷血的谋杀  想想看\N{\rEng}of a much more brutal, cold-blooded nature. Consider this:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.75,0:05:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,这两人各中四枪\N{\rEng}Four bullets per victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.88,0:05:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,共八枪  而非六枪\N{\rEng}Not six shots fired, but eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}因此他是先射完一轮\N{\rEng}That means that he fired the gun empty
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.96,0:06:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}再装弹补上两枪\N{\rEng}and then stopped to reload
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.38,0:06:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn华文楷体\fs20\fad(400,400)\bord2\pos(194.1,267)}编剧\N{\fs26}法兰克·戴拉朋特
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}然后再一人添一枪\N{\rEng}so that he could shoot each of them again. An extra bullet per lover
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.13,0:06:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,射穿脑袋\N{\rEng}right in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.40,0:06:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你面目冷漠  全无悔意  杜弗伦先生\N{\rEng}You strike me as a particularly icy and remorseless man, Mr. Dufresne.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.61,0:06:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,看见你就令我齿寒\N{\rEng}It chills my blood just to look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.68,0:06:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}根据缅因州赋予我的权力\N{\rEng}By the power vested in me by the state of Maine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.69,0:06:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn华文楷体\fs20\fad(400,400)\bord2\pos(194.1,267)}制片\N{\fs26}妮基·马文
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.75,0:06:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}我判你两个无期徒刑\N{\rEng}I hereby order you to serve two life sentences back-to-back
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.29,0:06:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,为两位死者偿命  退庭\N{\rEng}one for each of your victims. So be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.13,0:06:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn华文楷体\fs20\fad(400,400)\bord2\pos(194.1,267)}导演\N{\fs26}法兰克·戴拉朋特
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.95,0:07:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,坐下\N{\rEng}Sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你被判无期徒刑  已关二十年\N{\rEng}We see you've served 20 years of a life sentence?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.42,0:07:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,-是的  -你改过自新了吗\N{\rEng}-Yes, sir.  -You feel you've been rehabilitated?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  确实如此\N{\rEng}Yes, sir. Absolutely, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.76,0:07:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我已得到教训\N{\rEng}I mean, I learned my lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,真的  我已洗心革面\N{\rEng}I can honestly say that I'm a changed man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.51,0:07:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会危害社会\N{\rEng}I'm no longer a danger to society.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.08,0:07:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝为证\N{\rEng}That's God's honest truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.65,0:07:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}驳回
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.35,0:08:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德\N{\rEng}Hey, Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.85,0:08:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,怎样\N{\rEng}How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.35,0:08:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,还不是老样子\N{\rEng}Same old shit, different day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.79,0:08:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我了解\N{\rEng}Yeah, I know how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我下周也准备要吃闭门羹\N{\rEng}I'm up for rejection next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.63,0:08:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我上周才假释被拒\N{\rEng}Yeah, I got rejected last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.36,0:08:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,难兄难弟\N{\rEng}It happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.86,0:08:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,借一包烟吧\N{\rEng}Hey, Red, bump me a deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.50,0:08:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,滚开  你欠我五包\N{\rEng}Get out of my face, man! You're into me for five packs already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.00,0:08:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-四包  -五包\N{\rEng}-Four!  -Five!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.14,0:08:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,美国各监狱少不了我这种人\N{\rEng}There must be a con like me in every prison in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.77,0:08:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我什么都弄得到\N{\rEng}I'm the guy who can get it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.78,0:08:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,香烟啦  大麻啦\N{\rEng}Cigarettes, a bag of reefer, if that's your thing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.08,0:08:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,家有喜事想喝白兰地也行\N{\rEng}bottle of brandy to celebrate your kid's high school graduation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.72,0:08:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,几乎什么都没问题\N{\rEng}Damn near anything within reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.05,0:08:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  我就像邮购公司\N{\rEng}Yes, sir! I'm a regular Sears and Roebuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.73,0:08:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,1949年  安迪·杜弗伦\N{\rEng}So when Andy Dufresne came to me in 1949
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.86,0:08:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,要我把丽塔·海华丝弄给他\N{\rEng}and asked me to smuggle Rita Hayworth into the prison for him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.63,0:09:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我只说"没问题"\N{\rEng}I told him, "No problem."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,大家到大门口集合\N{\rEng}to the main gate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.59,0:09:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,到大门口集合\N{\rEng}to the main gate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.78,0:09:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪在47年初入肖申克监狱\N{\rEng}Andy came to Shawshank Prison
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.18,0:09:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,原因是杀害老婆和情夫\N{\rEng}in early 1947 for murdering his wife and the fella she was banging.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.38,0:09:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,他本来是大银行副总裁\N{\rEng}On the outside, he'd been vice president of a large Portland bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.89,0:09:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,典型的青年才俊\N{\rEng}Good work for a man so young.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.03,0:10:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德\N{\rEng}Here Red
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.93,0:10:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你懂英文吗\N{\rEng}You speak English, butt-steak?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.90,0:10:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,跟这位长官走\N{\rEng}You follow this officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.52,0:11:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我这辈子没看过这么窝囊的人渣\N{\rEng}I never seen such a sorry-Iooking heap of maggot shit in all my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.02,0:11:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,菜鸟  过来\N{\rEng}Hey, fish! Come over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.88,0:11:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,打个赌吧\N{\rEng}Taking bets today, Red?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.65,0:11:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,赌烟或钱\N{\rEng}Smokes or coin? Bettor's choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.55,0:11:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,烟  我赌两根\N{\rEng}Smokes. Put me down for two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.79,0:11:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你挑哪个\N{\rEng}All right, who's your horse?
