Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.91,0:22:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,闻我的屁吧\N{\rEng}Smell my ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.48,0:22:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,闻完再闻我的\N{\rEng}After he smells mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.91,0:22:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德  可惜你大大看走眼\N{\rEng}That's a shame about your horse coming in last and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.82,0:22:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我真感谢我的猪公\N{\rEng}But I sure do love that winning horse of mine, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.85,0:22:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,出院后我得亲亲他\N{\rEng}I owe that boy a big kiss when I see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.02,0:22:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,请他抽烟才对  小人得志\N{\rEng}Why don't you give him some of your cigarettes instead? Lucky fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.53,0:22:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,泰瑞\N{\rEng}Hey, Tyrell.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.43,0:22:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你在医务室值班吗\N{\rEng}You pull infirmary duty this week?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.37,0:22:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,那肥仔怎样了\N{\rEng}How's my horse doing anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.37,0:22:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,挂了\N{\rEng}Dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.34,0:23:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,海利打烂他的头\N{\rEng}Hadley busted his head up pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.74,0:23:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,医生已回家睡觉了\N{\rEng}Doc had gone home for the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.44,0:23:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他一直僵到天亮\N{\rEng}Poor bastard lay there till this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.91,0:23:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,根本无药可救\N{\rEng}By then, there wasn't nothing we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.69,0:23:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他叫什么名字\N{\rEng}What was his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.36,0:23:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你说什么\N{\rEng}What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.53,0:23:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我想知道他的名字\N{\rEng}I was just wondering if anyone knew his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.60,0:23:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,关你屁事  菜鸟\N{\rEng}What the fuck do you care, new fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.37,0:23:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,死人还要什么名字\N{\rEng}Doesn't fucking matter what his name was. He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.56,0:23:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,有人上过你了吗\N{\rEng}Anybody come at you yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.70,0:24:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你名草有主了吗\N{\rEng}Anybody get to you yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.20,0:24:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,牢里人人需要朋友\N{\rEng}Hey, we all need friends in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.04,0:24:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以当你朋友\N{\rEng}I could be a friend to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.91,0:24:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不易上手\N{\rEng}Hard to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.42,0:24:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢\N{\rEng}I like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.86,0:24:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,起初安迪不与人来往\N{\rEng}Andy kept pretty much to himself at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.43,0:24:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,大概心事重重\N{\rEng}I guess he had a lot on his mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.83,0:24:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,努力适应牢狱生活\N{\rEng}trying to adapt to life on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.40,0:24:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,直到一个月后\N{\rEng}Wasn't until a month went by before he opened his mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.81,0:24:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他才找人攀谈\N{\rEng}to say more than two words to somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.38,0:24:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,那个人\N{\rEng}As it turned out
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.41,0:24:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,就是我\N{\rEng}that somebody was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.06,0:24:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫安迪·杜弗伦\N{\rEng}I'm Andy Dufresne.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.06,0:25:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,杀妻的银行家\N{\rEng}Wife-killing banker.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.03,0:25:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,为了什么\N{\rEng}Why'd you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.80,0:25:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我没犯罪\N{\rEng}I didn't, since you ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.47,0:25:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你来对地方了\N{\rEng}You're going to fit right in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.54,0:25:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这里人人都无罪\N{\rEng}Everybody in here's innocent. Didn't you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.44,0:25:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-赫伍  你为何入狱   -我无罪  被律师害了\N{\rEng}-What you in here for?  -Didn't do it. Lawyer fucked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.08,0:25:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,听说你颇爱耍酷\N{\rEng}Rumor has it you're a real cold fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.85,0:25:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,难道你的屁比别人香\N{\rEng}You think your shit smells sweeter than most. Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.65,0:25:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你说呢\N{\rEng}What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.49,0:25:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,说老实话  我还不清楚\N{\rEng}To tell you the truth, I haven't made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.69,0:25:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你很有办法\N{\rEng}I understand you're a man that knows how to get things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.46,0:25:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我能够让你有求必应\N{\rEng}I'm known to locate certain things from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.96,0:25:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要一把石锤\N{\rEng}I wonder if you might get me a rock hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.93,0:25:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.30,0:25:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,石锤\N{\rEng}A rock hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.90,0:25:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,-用来干什么   -何必问呢\N{\rEng}-What is it and why?  -What do you care?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.94,0:25:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,若是牙刷  我就直接报价\N{\rEng}For a toothbrush, I wouldn't ask. I'd quote a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.84,0:25:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,因为牙刷不危险  对吗\N{\rEng}But a toothbrush is a non-lethal object, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.85,0:25:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,也有道理\N{\rEng}Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.68,0:26:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,石锤大约六  七寸长\N{\rEng}A rock hammer is about six or seven inches long.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.52,0:26:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-像鹤嘴锄  -鹤嘴锄\N{\rEng}-Looks like a miniature pickax.  -Pickax?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.05,0:26:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,敲石头用的\N{\rEng}For rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.86,0:26:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,石英\N{\rEng}Quartz?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.09,0:26:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,石英\N{\rEng}Quartz
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.03,0:26:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,云母  页岩\N{\rEng}And some mica, shale
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.74,0:26:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,石灰石\N{\rEng}limestone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.24,0:26:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,所以呢\N{\rEng}So?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.31,0:26:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾是石痴\N{\rEng}So I'm a rock hound.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.57,0:26:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我想重拾往日嗜好\N{\rEng}At least I was in my old life. I'd like to be again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.94,0:26:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我看你是想捶人家脑袋\N{\rEng}Or maybe you'd like to sink your toy into somebody's skull.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.55,0:26:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不是的  这儿没有人犯着我\N{\rEng}No, I have no enemies here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.32,0:26:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,没有  且慢\N{\rEng}No? Wait a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.25,0:26:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,话已传开了\N{\rEng}Word gets around.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.52,0:26:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,三姐妹对你有性趣\N{\rEng}The Sisters have taken quite a liking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.39,0:26:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,尤其是包格斯\N{\rEng}Especially Bogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.20,0:26:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,说我不是圈内人也没用吗\N{\rEng}Don't suppose it would help if I told them I'm not homosexual.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.83,0:26:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他们也不算是\N{\rEng}Neither are they.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.47,0:26:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,圈内人也是人  但他们是禽兽\N{\rEng}You have to be human first. They don't qualify.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.44,0:27:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,想干就干  根本不在乎你\N{\rEng}Bull queers take by force. That's all they want or understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.05,0:27:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我若是你的话  会加倍提防\N{\rEng}If I were you, I'd grow eyes in the back of my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.79,0:27:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-谢谢你的忠告  -反正不用钱\N{\rEng}-Thanks for the advice.  -Well, that's free.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.89,0:27:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你明白我的顾虑吧\N{\rEng}You understand my concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.06,0:27:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我不用石锤惹事  行吗\N{\rEng}If there's trouble, I won't use the rock hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.56,0:27:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,那你想逃狱  挖地道\N{\rEng}Then I'd guess you want to escape. Tunnel under the wall, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.50,0:27:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,有什么好笑\N{\rEng}What did I miss?  What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.60,0:27:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到它就明白了\N{\rEng}You'll understand when you see the rock hammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.14,0:27:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,它市价多少\N{\rEng}What's an item like this usually go for?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.57,0:27:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,奇石店卖七元\N{\rEng}Seven dollars in any rock-and-gem shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.58,0:27:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我通常加两成\N{\rEng}My normal markup's 20 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.25,0:27:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,不过嘛\N{\rEng}But this is a specialty item.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.82,0:27:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,价钱随风险调高  跟你收十元吧\N{\rEng}Risk goes up, price goes up. Let's make it an even 10 bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.49,0:27:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,就这样\N{\rEng}Ten it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.56,0:27:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,其实你是白花钱\N{\rEng}Waste of money, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.86,0:27:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么\N{\rEng}Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.56,0:27:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,狱方喜欢突袭搜房\N{\rEng}Folks around this joint love surprise inspections.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.20,0:27:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,找到石锤一定没收\N{\rEng}They find it, you're going to lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.37,0:27:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,到时候别摆我一道\N{\rEng}If they catch you, you don't know me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.67,0:28:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,否则再也别想跟我做生意\N{\rEng}Mention my name, we never do business again.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.41,0:28:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,连口香糖都不卖你\N{\rEng}Not for shoelaces or a stick of gum. Now you got that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.34,0:28:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我懂\N{\rEng}I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.11,0:28:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\rEng}Thank you, Mr
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.42,0:28:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德\N{\rEng}Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.98,0:28:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,叫我瑞德\N{\rEng}Name's Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.15,0:28:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德\N{\rEng}Red
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.92,0:28:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,为何叫瑞德\N{\rEng}Why do they call you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.33,0:28:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,也许我是爱尔兰人吧\N{\rEng}Maybe it's because I'm Irish.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.50,0:28:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,怪不得有人认为他臭屁\N{\rEng}I could see why some of the boys took him for snobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.24,0:28:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,他闷声不响的\N{\rEng}He had a quiet way about him
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.01,0:28:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他的步伐和谈吐简直是异类\N{\rEng}a walk and a talk that just wasn't normal around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.51,0:28:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他像\N{\rEng}He strolled
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.18,0:28:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在公园散步  无忧无虑\N{\rEng}like a man in the park without a care or a worry in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.59,0:28:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,仿佛身披隐形衣\N{\rEng}Like he had on an invisible coat that would shield him from this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.76,0:28:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rEng}yes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.19,0:28:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我打一开始\N{\rEng}I think it'd be fair to say
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.70,0:28:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,就喜欢他\N{\rEng}I liked Andy from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.53,0:29:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,别耽误我们时间\N{\rEng}Let's go! Some of us got a schedule to keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.61,0:29:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,快点\N{\rEng}Move it! Come on, move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.71,0:29:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你好  老婆待你如何\N{\rEng}How you doing? How's the wife treating you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.33,0:29:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,继续走\N{\rEng}keep moving
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.23,0:29:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,继续走\N{\rEng}just go
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.57,0:29:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德\N{\rEng}Red
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.79,0:29:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪说的对\N{\rEng}Andy was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.49,0:29:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我见到货就明白了\N{\rEng}I finally got the joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.02,0:30:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,用它挖地道\N{\rEng}It would take a man about 600 years
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.63,0:30:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,得挖六百年\N{\rEng}to tunnel under the wall with one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.87,0:30:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-要书吗   -不要\N{\rEng}-Book?  -Not today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.34,0:30:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-要书吗   -不要\N{\rEng}-Book? -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.78,0:30:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,老布\N{\rEng}Brook
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.68,0:30:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,给杜弗伦的货\N{\rEng}Delivery for Dufresne.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.96,0:30:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,要书吗\N{\rEng}Book?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.66,0:30:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,要书吗\N{\rEng}Book?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.33,0:30:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,杜弗伦\N{\rEng}Dufresne
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.59,0:30:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你的书\N{\rEng}Here's your book.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.14,0:30:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.62,0:31:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,杜弗伦  漂白水不够了  你去后面拿\N{\rEng}We're running low on hexite. Get on back and fetch us up some.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.66,0:31:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,小心我弄瞎你们\N{\rEng}This will blind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.59,0:31:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,宝贝  别出声\N{\rEng}Honey, hush.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.54,0:31:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你反抗\N{\rEng}That's it. You fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.71,0:32:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,那更刺激\N{\rEng}Better that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.42,0:32:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我也希望另一种结局\N{\rEng}I wish I could tell you Andy fought the good fight
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.72,0:32:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,就是安迪打赢  全身而退\N{\rEng}and the Sisters let him be.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.29,0:32:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望如此\N{\rEng}I wish I could tell you that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.33,0:32:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,然而监狱不是童话世界\N{\rEng}but prison is no fairy-tale world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.43,0:32:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他绝口不提是谁\N{\rEng}He never said who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.63,0:32:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,但谁都明白\N{\rEng}But we all knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.07,0:32:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这情况持续了一阵\N{\rEng}Things went on like that for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.98,0:32:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,坐牢是一段段例行公事\N{\rEng}Prison life consists of routine
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.75,0:32:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,一段忙完又一段\N{\rEng}and then more routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.22,0:32:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪随时挂着新伤\N{\rEng}Every so often, Andy would show up with fresh bruises.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.22,0:32:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,三姐妹不放过他\N{\rEng}The Sisters kept at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.29,0:32:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他有时打赢\N{\rEng}Sometimes he was able to fight them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.56,0:32:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,有时吃败仗\N{\rEng}Sometimes not.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.23,0:32:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是安迪的遭遇\N{\rEng}And that's how it went for Andy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.97,0:32:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,那是他的例行公事\N{\rEng}That was his routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.57,0:33:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他毕生没像头两年那么惨\N{\rEng}I do believe those first two years were the worst for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.51,0:33:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,假使再这样下去\N{\rEng}And I also believe that if things had gone on that way
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.21,0:33:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这黑牢就会毁掉他\N{\rEng}this place would have got the best of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.41,0:33:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,不过  在49年春天\N{\rEng}But then, in the spring of 1949
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.41,0:33:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,狱方宣布\N{\rEng}the powers that be decided:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.52,0:33:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,车牌工厂屋顶要翻修\N{\rEng}The roof of the license-plate factory needs resurfacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.05,0:33:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要12人做工一周\N{\rEng}I need a dozen volunteers for a week's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.96,0:33:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你们都知道\N{\rEng}As you know
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.16,0:33:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,特别的公差享特别的待遇\N{\rEng}special detail carries with it special privileges.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.93,0:33:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,这是户外公差\N{\rEng}It was outdoor detail
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.73,0:33:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,五月份出户外公差  实在求之不得\N{\rEng}and May is one damned fine month to be working outdoors.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.30,0:33:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,排好队\N{\rEng}Stay in line there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.77,0:33:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,一百多人志愿报名\N{\rEng}More than a hundred men volunteered for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.21,0:33:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,昂格\N{\rEng}Wallace E. Unger.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.72,0:33:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞丁\N{\rEng}Ellis Redding.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.29,0:33:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是很巧吗\N{\rEng}Wouldn't you know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.29,0:33:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我的哥儿们全都中签\N{\rEng}Me and some fellows I know were among the names called.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.79,0:33:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪·杜弗伦\N{\rEng}Andrew Dufresne.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.19,0:33:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,其实是每人一包烟买的\N{\rEng}It only cost us a pack of smokes per man.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.63,0:34:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我照常抽两成\N{\rEng}I made my usual 20 percent, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.30,0:34:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,德州一个律师打电话来\N{\rEng}So this big-shot lawyer calls me long-distance from Texas.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.97,0:34:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我问什么事\N{\rEng}I say, "Yeah?"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.81,0:34:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他说"抱歉  令兄过世"\N{\rEng}He says, "Sorry to inform you, but your brother just died."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.64,0:34:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-糟糕  我很遗憾  -我才不为那烂人遗憾\N{\rEng}-I'm sorry to hear that.  -I'm not. He was an asshole.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.75,0:34:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他离家多年  生死不明\N{\rEng}Ran off years ago. Figured him for dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.15,0:34:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,这大律师说\N{\rEng}So this lawyer fellow says to me:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.65,0:34:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"令兄是位富翁" 挖油井赚了一百万\N{\rEng}"He died a rich man." Oil wells and shit. Close to a million bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.46,0:34:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,一百万\N{\rEng}A million bucks?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.63,0:34:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-对  算他走狗运  -有你一份吗\N{\rEng}-Incredible how lucky some assholes get.  -You going to see any of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.73,0:34:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他留给我三万五\N{\rEng}Thirty-five thousand. That's what he left me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.70,0:34:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-美金   -对\N{\rEng}-Dollars? -Yep
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.64,0:34:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,简直像中乐透嘛\N{\rEng}That's great! That's like winning the sweepstakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.97,0:34:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,不是吗\N{\rEng}Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.27,0:34:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,政府是白混的吗\N{\rEng}Dumb shit, what do you think the government will do to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.44,0:34:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,它想大口分掉这大饼\N{\rEng}Take a big wet bite out of my ass is what.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.58,0:34:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,可怜虫\N{\rEng}Poor Byron.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.82,0:34:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,过路财神  真够倒霉\N{\rEng}Terrible fucking luck, huh? Crying shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.19,0:34:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,有人就是命衰\N{\rEng}Some people really got it awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.72,0:34:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你疯了\N{\rEng}Andy, are you nuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.29,0:35:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,专心干活\N{\rEng}IKeep your eyes on your mop, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.39,0:35:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,缴了税还剩不少\N{\rEng}You'll pay some tax, but you'll still end up
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.56,0:35:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  够换新车\N{\rEng}Yeah, maybe enough to buy a new car, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.56,0:35:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,但买车要缴税\N{\rEng}I got to pay tax on the car. Repair
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.97,0:35:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,还要修理  保养  孩子吵着要兜风\N{\rEng}maintenance, kids pestering you to take them for a ride all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.94,0:35:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,万一报错税  全得自付\N{\rEng}Then if you figure your tax wrong, you pay out of your own pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.81,0:35:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉你  这就是政府\N{\rEng}I tell you! Uncle Sam!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.18,0:35:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,石头都榨得出血来\N{\rEng}He puts his hand in your shirt and squeezes your tit till it's purple.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.51,0:35:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪\N{\rEng}Andy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.82,0:35:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-他不想活了  -继续工作\N{\rEng}-Getting himself killed. -I Keep tarring.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.22,0:35:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,什么哥哥  狗屁\N{\rEng}Some brother. Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.69,0:35:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,海利先生\N{\rEng}Mr. Hadley
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.96,0:35:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你信任老婆吗\N{\rEng}do you trust your wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.97,0:35:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,真好笑\N{\rEng}Oh, that's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.97,0:35:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你没了牙吹我喇叭更好笑\N{\rEng}You'll look funnier sucking my dick with no teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.80,0:35:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,她会扯你后腿吗\N{\rEng}What I mean is, do you think she'd go behind your back?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.27,0:35:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,够了  他活的不耐烦了\N{\rEng}Step aside, Mert. This fucker's having himself an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.88,0:35:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,他要推落安迪\N{\rEng}He'll push him off!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.15,0:35:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,她靠得住\N{\rEng}If you trust her, you can keep
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.21,0:35:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你就能领三万五\N{\rEng}that 35,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.35,0:36:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,-你说什么   -三万五\N{\rEng}-What did you say?  -Thirty-five thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.69,0:36:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,全部领到\N{\rEng}All of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.92,0:36:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,-一个子儿也不少  -你最好别耍我\N{\rEng}-Every penny.  -You better start making sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.19,0:36:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,想领全额  就赠与太太\N{\rEng}If you want to keep it,  give it to your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.73,0:36:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,国税局允许一生一次  最多六万的赠与免税\N{\rEng}The IRS allows a one-time-only gift to your spouse for up to $ 60,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.83,0:36:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-乖乖  免税吗   -对\N{\rEng}-Bullshit. Tax-free?  -Tax-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.40,0:36:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,国税局征不到一文钱\N{\rEng}IRS can't touch one cent.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.77,0:36:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你是那杀妻的银行家\N{\rEng}You're that smart banker that killed his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.47,0:36:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,信任你难道不会害我坐牢\N{\rEng}Why should I believe you? So I can end up in here with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.04,0:36:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,完全合法  你去问也一样\N{\rEng}It's legal. Ask the IRS. They'll say the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.08,0:36:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我不该开口的  我以为你会去问\N{\rEng}I feel stupid telling you this. I'm sure you would have investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.35,0:36:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我不用你教我这些鸟事\N{\rEng}I don't need you to tell me where the bear shit in the buckwheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.22,0:36:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  但你要找人填表\N{\rEng}Of course not. But you do need someone to set it up for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.82,0:36:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,请律师可得花钱\N{\rEng}That'll cost you. A lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.59,0:36:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,没卵的怂棍\N{\rEng}A bunch of ball-washing bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.33,0:36:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我帮你办  为你省钱\N{\rEng}I suppose I could set it up for you. That would save you some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.00,0:36:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你领表我来填\N{\rEng}You get the forms, I'll prepare them
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.30,0:36:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,完全免费\N{\rEng}nearly free of charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.27,0:36:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,只要请我同事一人三瓶啤酒\N{\rEng}I'd only ask three beers apiece for each of my coworkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.54,0:36:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,同事 够新鲜的\N{\rEng}"Coworkers." That's rich!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.91,0:37:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,做黑手的有酒喝\N{\rEng}A man working outdoors feels more like a man
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.65,0:37:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,才有尊严  这是我的浅见\N{\rEng}if he can have a bottle of suds. That's only my opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.55,0:37:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,大人\N{\rEng}sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.49,0:37:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,看什么看  回去干活\N{\rEng}What are you jimmies staring at?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.62,0:37:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,干活\N{\rEng}Let's go! Work!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.74,0:37:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,于是呢\N{\rEng}And that's how it came to pass
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.87,0:37:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,在完工前一天\N{\rEng}that on the second-to-last day of the job
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.74,0:37:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,49年春的公差犯人\N{\rEng}the convict crew that tarred the factory roof in the spring of '49
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.51,0:37:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在早上十点坐成一堆\N{\rEng}wound up sitting in a row at 10:00 in the morning
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.85,0:37:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,喝着冰凉的啤酒  肖申克监狱\N{\rEng}drinking icy-cold beer, courtesy of the hardest screw
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.52,0:37:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,历来最狠的狱官请的客\N{\rEng}that ever walked a turn at Shawshank State Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.99,0:37:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,娘们儿  趁凉快喝\N{\rEng}Drink up while it's cold, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.53,0:37:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,这王八蛋还装大方呢\N{\rEng}The colossal prick even managed to sound magnanimous.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.23,0:38:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,阳光洒肩头  仿佛自由人\N{\rEng}We sat and drank with the sun on our shoulders and felt like free men.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.07,0:38:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,像在修缮自家屋顶\N{\rEng}We could have been tarring the roof of one of our own houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.71,0:38:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我们像是造物之主般自在\N{\rEng}We were the lords of all creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.11,0:38:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪呢\N{\rEng}As for Andy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.95,0:38:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他窝在凉荫下\N{\rEng}he spent that break hunkered in the shade
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.78,0:38:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,脸上挂着奇异微笑\N{\rEng}a strange little smile on his face
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.52,0:38:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,看着我们喝他的酒\N{\rEng}watching us drink his beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.13,0:38:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,来一瓶吧\N{\rEng}Want a cold one?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.87,0:38:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢  我戒酒了\N{\rEng}No, thanks. I gave up drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.77,0:38:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能想说  他想拍狱方马屁\N{\rEng}You could argue he done it to curry favor with the guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.54,0:38:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,或想博取囚犯友谊\N{\rEng}Or maybe make a few friends among us cons.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.08,0:38:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但我呢\N{\rEng}Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.35,0:38:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,认为他只想重温自由\N{\rEng}I think he did it just to feel normal again
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.59,0:38:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,即使只有一刹那\N{\rEng}if only for a short while.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.46,0:38:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我当王\N{\rEng}IKing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.43,0:38:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-下棋  是帝王游戏  -什么\N{\rEng}-Chess. Now there's a game of kings. -What?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.26,0:38:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,讲文明  重谋略\N{\rEng}Civilized. Strategic.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.66,0:39:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,神秘的要死  真讨厌\N{\rEng}And a total fucking mystery. I hate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.93,0:39:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,改天我教你吧\N{\rEng}Let me teach you someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.24,0:39:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,好呀\N{\rEng}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.71,0:39:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我想买个棋盘\N{\rEng}We could get a board together.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.67,0:39:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你找对人了  我不论什么都弄得到\N{\rEng}You're talking to the right man. I can get things, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.94,0:39:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,棋盘用买的  但棋子我来刻\N{\rEng}We might do business on a board, and I'll carve the pieces myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.15,0:39:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,一半用雪花石膏  一半用皂石\N{\rEng}One side in alabaster, one in soapstone. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.05,0:39:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,要刻上许多年\N{\rEng}I think it'll take years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.65,0:39:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,时间有的是  就是缺石头\N{\rEng}Years I got. What I don't have are the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.39,0:39:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,操场很贫瘠\N{\rEng}Pickings are pretty slim in the yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.56,0:39:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,多半是石子\N{\rEng}Pebbles, mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.73,0:39:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,咱们算是朋友吧\N{\rEng}We're getting to be kind of friends, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.40,0:39:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,算是吧\N{\rEng}Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.60,0:39:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我想问你\N{\rEng}Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.61,0:39:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你为何杀人\N{\rEng}Why'd you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.28,0:39:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我无罪\N{\rEng}I'm innocent, Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.05,0:39:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,跟大家一样\N{\rEng}Just like everybody else here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.42,0:39:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你呢\N{\rEng}What are you in for?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.69,0:40:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,跟你一样  杀人\N{\rEng}Murder. Same as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.06,0:40:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,无罪吗\N{\rEng}Innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.93,0:40:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我是肖申克唯一的罪犯\N{\rEng}Only guilty man in Shawshank.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.19,0:40:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}彼德
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.66,0:40:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}班尼
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.66,0:41:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}A
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.76,0:41:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,歌女呢\N{\rEng}Where's the canary?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.36,0:41:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道\N{\rEng}How did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.86,0:41:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-我知道什么   -原来你不知道\N{\rEng}-How did I know what?  -So you don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.36,0:41:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,来\N{\rEng}Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.03,0:41:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,歌女在这里\N{\rEng}This is where the canary is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.80,0:41:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,没想到她会来寒舍献唱吧\N{\rEng}Quite a surprise to hear a woman singing in my house, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.65,0:41:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,的确\N{\rEng}That's quite a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.98,0:41:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,没想到\N{\rEng}surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.05,0:41:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德\N{\rEng}Red
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.95,0:41:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,等一下啦\N{\rEng}Wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.89,0:41:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,她上场了\N{\rEng}Here she comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.66,0:41:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我最迷她甩头发的骚样\N{\rEng}I like this part when she does that shit with her hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.73,0:41:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,这个月看过三场了\N{\rEng}I know. I've seen it three times this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.66,0:41:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,姬旦  你衣着整齐吗\N{\rEng}Gilda, are you decent?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.57,0:41:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我\N{\rEng}Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.40,0:41:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱死了\N{\rEng}God, I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.34,0:42:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,听说阁下有求必应\N{\rEng}I understand you're a man that knows how to get things.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.35,0:42:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,在下确非浪得虚名  你要什么\N{\rEng}I'm known to locate certain things from time to time. What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.28,0:42:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,-丽塔·海华丝  -什么\N{\rEng}-Rita Hayworth. -What?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.99,0:42:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,弄得到吗\N{\rEng}Can you get her?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.76,0:42:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这位就是法罗呀  久仰\N{\rEng}So this is Johnny Farrel. I've heard a lot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.36,0:42:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-要几个星期  -几星期\N{\rEng}-Take a few weeks. -Weeks?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.86,0:42:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我又没把她压在下面\N{\rEng}I don't have her stuffed down the front of my pants right now, sorry to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.84,0:42:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,反正弄得到\N{\rEng}But I'll get her.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.37,0:42:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,安啦\N{\rEng}Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.57,0:42:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,谢了\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.26,0:42:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,-出去  -我得放映呀\N{\rEng}-Get out!  -I got to change reels!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.46,0:42:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我叫你滚\N{\rEng}I said fuck off!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.61,0:43:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你不尖叫吗\N{\rEng}Ain't you going to scream?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.31,0:43:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,咱们算算总帐\N{\rEng}Let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.28,0:43:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,他打破我鼻子\N{\rEng}He broke my fucking nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.59,0:43:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,现在\N{\rEng}Now
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.29,0:43:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我要解拉链\N{\rEng}I'm going to open my fly
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.73,0:43:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,叫你含什么你就含\N{\rEng}and you'll swallow what I give you to swallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.63,0:43:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,先舔我  再舔公鸡  因为你害他流鼻血\N{\rEng}Then you'll swallow Rooster's.  You broke his nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.44,0:43:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该要道歉\N{\rEng}He ought to have something to show for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.77,0:43:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,它进我的嘴  就跟你分家\N{\rEng}You put it in my mouth, you lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.84,0:43:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,不  你没搞懂\N{\rEng}No, you don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.78,0:43:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我会用钻子刺穿你耳朵\N{\rEng}Do that and I'll put all eight inches of this in your ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.01,0:43:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  但你应该知道  脑部遇袭\N{\rEng}All right, but you should know that sudden, serious brain injury
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.68,0:43:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,会使人死劲咬\N{\rEng}causes the victim to bite down hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.82,0:43:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,用力之大呀\N{\rEng}In fact, I hear the bite reflex is so strong
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.12,0:43:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,得用铁撬\N{\rEng}they have to pry the victim's jaws open
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.79,0:43:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,才扳得开\N{\rEng}with a crowbar.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.13,0:44:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道\N{\rEng}Where do you get this shit?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.87,0:44:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,书上写的\N{\rEng}I read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.67,0:44:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你识字吗  豆腐脑\N{\rEng}You know how to read, you ignorant fuck?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.01,0:44:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,亲爱的\N{\rEng}Honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.04,0:44:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你不该损我\N{\rEng}You shouldn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.45,0:44:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,包格斯没逼他吹喇叭\N{\rEng}Bogs didn't put anything in Andy's mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.62,0:44:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,其他两个也不敢\N{\rEng}And neither did his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.12,0:44:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他们把安迪打个半死\N{\rEng}What they did do is beat him within an inch of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.62,0:44:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在医务室里待了一个月\N{\rEng}Andy spent a month in the infirmary.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.93,0:44:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,包格斯被罚独囚一周\N{\rEng}Bogs spent a week in the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.53,0:44:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,时间到\N{\rEng}Time's up, Bogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.87,0:44:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,遵命\N{\rEng}It's your world, boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.81,0:44:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,回牢房准备点名\N{\rEng}Return to your cellblocks for evening count.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.81,0:44:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,全部回房去\N{\rEng}All prisoners report for lock down.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.40,0:45:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,什么事\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.08,0:45:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-他想去哪儿   -抓住脚\N{\rEng}-Where's he going?  -Grab his ankles.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.28,0:45:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,不要  救命\N{\rEng}No help!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.36,0:45:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,此后没有再发生两件事\N{\rEng}Two things never happened again after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.23,0:45:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,三姐妹再也没碰安迪\N{\rEng}The Sisters never laid a finger on Andy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.20,0:45:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,包格斯再也无法走路\N{\rEng}And Bogs would never walk again.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.87,0:45:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他被转送到低戒护的医院\N{\rEng}They transferred him to a minimum-security hospital upstate.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.57,0:45:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我只知道他的余生\N{\rEng}To my knowledge, he lived out the rest of his days
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.54,0:45:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,全靠吸管进食\N{\rEng}drinking his food through a straw.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.38,0:45:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我想热烈欢迎安迪出院\N{\rEng}Andy could use a nice welcome back when he gets out of the infirmary.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.22,0:46:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,没问题\N{\rEng}Sounds good to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.05,0:46:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,咱们欠他的酒\N{\rEng}I figure we owe him that much for the beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.29,0:46:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,他喜欢下棋\N{\rEng}The man likes to play chess.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.06,0:46:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,帮他找石头吧\N{\rEng}Let's get him some rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.59,0:46:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,各位\N{\rEng}Guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.60,0:46:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我找到一粒\N{\rEng}I got one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.86,0:46:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,瞧瞧\N{\rEng}I got one. Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.27,0:46:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,那不是皂石或雪花石膏\N{\rEng}Heywood, that isn't soapstone! And it ain't alabaster either.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.54,0:46:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈是地质学家吗\N{\rEng}What are you, a fucking geologist?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.64,0:46:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他说的没错\N{\rEng}He's right. It ain't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.58,0:47:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,-那这是什么   -马屎蛋\N{\rEng}-What the hell is it then? -It's a horse apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.45,0:47:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-胡说   -没有  是马屎\N{\rEng}-Bullshit!  -No, horseshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.05,0:47:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,马屎化石\N{\rEng}Petrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.02,0:47:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,天哪\N{\rEng}God
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.53,0:47:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他妈的\N{\rEng}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.03,0:47:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,错误难免  但众志成城\N{\rEng}Despite a few hitches, the boys came through in fine style.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.47,0:47:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,在安迪出院前一周\N{\rEng}And by the weekend he was due back
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.67,0:47:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我们找的石头多得够他刻一辈子\N{\rEng}we had enough rocks saved up to keep him busy till rapture.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.21,0:47:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,同时到了一大批货\N{\rEng}Also got a big shipment in that week.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.97,0:47:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,烟\N{\rEng}Cigarettes
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.31,0:47:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,口香糖\N{\rEng}chewing gum
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.54,0:47:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,威士忌\N{\rEng}sipping whisky
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.21,0:47:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,裸女扑克牌\N{\rEng}playing cards with naked ladies on them. You name it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.95,0:47:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,当然  最重要的是\N{\rEng}And of course, the most important item:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.42,0:47:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,丽塔·海华丝\N{\rEng}Rita Hayworth herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.35,0:48:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}欢迎归来  免费享用
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.66,0:48:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,大家醒醒\N{\rEng}Wake up
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.59,0:48:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,小心  来查房了\N{\rEng}Heads up. They're tossing cells.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.06,0:48:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,小心  来查房了\N{\rEng}Heads up. They're tossing cells!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.37,0:48:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,119房\N{\rEng}119.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.70,0:48:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,123房\N{\rEng}123.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.51,0:48:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,圣经\N{\rEng}Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.65,0:48:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,起立\N{\rEng}On your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.29,0:48:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,面对墙\N{\rEng}Face the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.92,0:49:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,转身面向典狱长\N{\rEng}Turn around and face the warden.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.43,0:49:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴你念圣经\N{\rEng}Pleased to see you reading this.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.83,0:49:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你最喜欢哪一章节\N{\rEng}Any favorite passages?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.64,0:49:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"所以你们要惊醒\N{\rEng}"Watch ye, therefore,for ye know not
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.20,0:49:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,因为不知道家主何时来"\N{\rEng}when the master of the house cometh."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.57,0:49:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,马可福音  13章35节\N{\rEng}Mark 13:35.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.48,0:49:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我也一向喜欢它\N{\rEng}I've always liked that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.28,0:49:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,但我更爱\N{\rEng}But I prefer
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.42,0:49:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"我是世界的光\N{\rEng}"I am the light of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.75,0:49:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,跟从我的  就不在黑暗里走  必要得跟着生命的光"\N{\rEng}Ye that followeth me shall have the light of life."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.26,0:50:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,约翰福音8章12节\N{\rEng}John, chapter 8, verse 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.16,0:50:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,听说你精通数字\N{\rEng}I hear you're good with numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.39,0:50:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,真好\N{\rEng}How nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.63,0:50:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,人应该有专长\N{\rEng}Man should have a skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.10,0:50:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么\N{\rEng}Explain this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.30,0:50:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,磨石毡  打磨石头用的\N{\rEng}It's called a rock blanket. It's for shaping and polishing rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.81,0:50:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我的小嗜好\N{\rEng}A little hobby of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.59,0:50:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,很标准\N{\rEng}It's pretty clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.29,0:50:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,无重大违规\N{\rEng}Some contraband here, but nothing to get in a twist over.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.73,0:50:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这我不大赞成\N{\rEng}I can't say I approve of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.37,0:50:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,不过嘛\N{\rEng}But I suppose
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.90,0:50:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,破个例也无妨\N{\rEng}exceptions can be made.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.28,0:50:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,锁门\N{\rEng}Lock them up!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.52,0:51:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,差点忘了\N{\rEng}I almost forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.52,0:51:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎能拿你的圣经\N{\rEng}I'd hate to deprive you of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.42,0:51:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"得救之道  就在其中"\N{\rEng}Salvation lies within.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.56,0:51:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.17,0:51:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,查房只是借口\N{\rEng}Tossing cells was just an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.21,0:51:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,事实是\N{\rEng}Truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.64,0:51:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,诺顿要秤他斤两\N{\rEng}Norton wanted to size Andy up.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.75,0:51:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}主的审判迅速降临
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.79,0:51:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我太太在教堂织的\N{\rEng}My wife made that in church group.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.79,0:51:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,相当精巧\N{\rEng}Very nice, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.66,0:51:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,喜欢洗衣房的工作吗\N{\rEng}You enjoy working the laundry?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.80,0:51:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,不怎么喜欢\N{\rEng}No, sir. Not especially.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.84,0:51:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,也许我们可以\N{\rEng}Perhaps we can find something more
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.54,0:51:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,让你更能发挥才学\N{\rEng}befitting a man of your education.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.05,0:52:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,小杰  老布呢\N{\rEng}Hey, Jake. Where's Brooks?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.32,0:52:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪  我听见你来了\N{\rEng}I thought I heard you out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.82,0:52:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我转派给你了\N{\rEng}I've been reassigned to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.66,0:52:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我听说了\N{\rEng}I know, they told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.83,0:52:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,真想不到呀\N{\rEng}Ain't that a kick in the head?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.10,0:52:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,来个小小巡礼吧\N{\rEng}Well, I'll give you the dime tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.60,0:52:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.17,0:52:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,都在你眼前了\N{\rEng}Well, here she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.10,0:52:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,肖申克监狱图书馆\N{\rEng}The Shawshank Prison Library.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.77,0:52:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,国家地理杂志\N{\rEng}National Geographics
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.68,0:52:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,读者文摘\N{\rEng}Reader's Digest condensed books
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.68,0:52:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,畅销西部小说\N{\rEng}and Louis L'Amour.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.85,0:52:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,展望杂志\N{\rEng}Look magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.02,0:52:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,悬疑小说\N{\rEng}Erle Stanley Gardners.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.62,0:52:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,每晚搬上车兜一圈\N{\rEng}Every evening I load up the cart and make my rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.29,0:52:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,记下借书人名字\N{\rEng}I enter the names on this clipboard here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.46,0:52:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,如此而已  简简单单\N{\rEng}Easy, peasy, Japanese-y.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.46,0:52:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-有问题吗   -你管图书馆多久了\N{\rEng}-Any questions?  -How long have you been librarian?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.03,0:53:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,1905年入狱  1912年入馆\N{\rEng}I come here in '05, and they made me librarian in 1912.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.37,0:53:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这么多年都没有助手\N{\rEng}And have you ever had an assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.81,0:53:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,没有  根本用不着\N{\rEng}No. Not much to it, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.98,0:53:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,那为何派我来\N{\rEng}Why me? Why now?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.65,0:53:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.15,0:53:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但有人陪我真好\N{\rEng}But it'd be nice to have some company down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.68,0:53:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,杜弗伦\N{\rEng}Dufresne
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.43,0:53:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,就是他  就一个\N{\rEng}That's him. That's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.37,0:53:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我是狄金斯\N{\rEng}I'm Dekins.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.94,0:53:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我在想\N{\rEng}I was thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.24,0:53:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,为孩子弄个教育基金\N{\rEng}about setting up some kind of trust fund for my kids' educations.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.02,0:53:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我懂了\N{\rEng}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.59,0:53:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,咱们坐下谈吧\N{\rEng}Why don't we have a seat and talk it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.26,0:54:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,老布  有纸笔吗\N{\rEng}Do you have a piece of paper and a pencil?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.08,0:54:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.05,0:54:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rEng}So
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.88,0:54:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,狄金斯先生\N{\rEng}Mister Dekins
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.45,0:54:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,然后安迪说\N{\rEng}And then Andy says, "Mr. Dekins
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.75,0:54:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"你想让公子进哈佛或耶鲁"\N{\rEng}do you want your sons to go to Harvard or Yale?"
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.96,0:54:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你少瞎扯\N{\rEng}He didn't say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.36,0:54:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,真的  老天为证\N{\rEng}As God as my witness!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.13,0:54:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他愣了一下\N{\rEng}Dekins blinked for a second
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.06,0:54:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,傻笑出来  后来他真的跟安迪握手\N{\rEng}then he laughed and actually shook Andy's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.63,0:54:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-握你的鸟  -真的握手\N{\rEng}-My ass!  -Shook his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.14,0:54:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我乐的差点尿出来\N{\rEng}I tell you, I near soiled myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.24,0:54:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,若给安迪弄一套西装领带\N{\rEng}All he needed was a suit and tie and a jiggly hula gal on his desk
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.71,0:54:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,他就成了咨询先生\N{\rEng}he'd have been "Mr. Dufresne," if you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.51,0:54:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,开始交新朋友了  安迪\N{\rEng}Making a few friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.45,0:54:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,也不算朋友\N{\rEng}I wouldn't say "friends."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.32,0:54:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我是精通理财的囚徒\N{\rEng}I'm a convicted murderer who provides sound financial planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.35,0:55:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,这种本事很受用\N{\rEng}It's a wonderful pet to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.89,0:55:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,起码不用干洗衣工\N{\rEng}Got you out of the laundry, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.23,0:55:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,还派得上更大用场\N{\rEng}It might do more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.36,0:55:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,比如扩建图书馆  买新书\N{\rEng}How about expanding the library. Get some new books.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.26,0:55:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,还不如要个撞球桌\N{\rEng}If you ask for something, ask for a pool table.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.43,0:55:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rEng}yes
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.60,0:55:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你想怎么弄\N{\rEng}How do you expect to do that? I mean
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.77,0:55:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,阁下想怎样买新书\N{\rEng}get new books in here, "Mr. Dufresne, if you please."
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.21,0:55:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,找典狱长要钱\N{\rEng}I'll ask the warden for funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.15,0:55:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,少年呀  我经历六个典狱长\N{\rEng}Six wardens have been through here in my tenure, and I've learned
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.65,0:55:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我学到亘古不变的真理\N{\rEng}one immutable, universal truth:
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.19,0:55:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,就是给钱是不可能的\N{\rEng}Not one born whose asshole
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.79,0:55:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他们没一个生来有屁眼\N{\rEng}wouldn't pucker up tighter than a snare drum when you ask for funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.59,0:55:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-预算太少了  -我了解\N{\rEng}-The budget's stretched thin as it is.  -I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.70,0:55:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以写信跟州议会要钱\N{\rEng}Maybe I could write the state senate and request funds from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.33,0:55:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,监狱领到款只能做三种用途\N{\rEng}They have only three ways to spend the taxpayers' money for prisons:
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.64,0:55:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,筑高墙  加牢笼  添警卫\N{\rEng}More walls, more bars, more guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.27,0:55:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我仍请您恩准  一周一信\N{\rEng}I'd like to try, with permission. A letter a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.14,0:55:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-总会有结果  -难说哦\N{\rEng}-They can't ignore me forever.  -Sure can.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.15,0:55:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,想写就写吧\N{\rEng}But you write your letters if it makes you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.12,0:56:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我一定寄出  行吗\N{\rEng}I'll even mail them for you. How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.39,0:56:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪开始一周一信\N{\rEng}So Andy started writing a letter a week
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.39,0:56:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他说话算话\N{\rEng}just like he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.16,0:56:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,不过  就像诺顿说的\N{\rEng}And like Norton said
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.00,0:56:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,毫无回音\N{\rEng}Andy got no answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.67,0:56:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,次年  他替半数的警卫报税\N{\rEng}The following April, he did tax returns for half the guards at Shawshank.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.91,0:56:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,再过一年  全都找他帮忙\N{\rEng}Year after that, he did them all
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.42,0:56:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,包括典狱长的\N{\rEng}including the warden's.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.09,0:56:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,又过一年的狱际棒球赛\N{\rEng}Year after that, they rescheduled the intramural season
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.76,0:56:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,改在与税季重叠\N{\rEng}to coincide with tax season.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.76,0:56:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,各监狱的警卫都带税单找他\N{\rEng}The guards on the opposing teams all remembered to bring their W-2s.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.43,0:56:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,狱方发枪给你\N{\rEng}So Moresby Prison
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.97,0:56:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,但要你付钱\N{\rEng}issued you a gun, but you paid for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.47,0:56:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,连枪套也要我付\N{\rEng}Right. The holster too.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.37,0:56:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,这笔钱可以扣除\N{\rEng}That's tax-deductible. You can write that off.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.04,0:57:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  安迪就像家庭工业\N{\rEng}Yes, sir! Andy was a regular cottage industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.78,0:57:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,税季繁忙时  还可请助手\N{\rEng}In fact, it got so busy at tax time, he was allowed a staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.55,0:57:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,请帮我拿一叠表格\N{\rEng}Could you hand me a stack of 1040s?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.22,0:57:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,每年此时我调离工厂  我乐到心坎里\N{\rEng}Got me out of the wood shop a month out of the year, and that was fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.29,0:57:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,至于信  他仍继续寄\N{\rEng}And still, he kept sending those letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.23,0:57:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德  安迪  老布出事了\N{\rEng}It's Brooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.40,0:57:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,守着门\N{\rEng}Watch the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.14,0:57:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,老布\N{\rEng}Please, Brooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.74,0:57:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-你他妈的别冲动嘛  -混帐  退后\N{\rEng}-Calm the fuck down.  -Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.98,0:57:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-混蛋  退后   -怎么了\N{\rEng}-Stay back, goddamn it!  -What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.81,0:57:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,好好的  突然亮刀子\N{\rEng}One second he's fine, then out come the knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.58,0:57:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,老布  有话好说\N{\rEng}We can talk about this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.65,0:57:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,放屁  没啥可说  我要割断他喉咙\N{\rEng}There's nothing to talk about. I'll cut his fucking throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.65,0:57:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,等一下  赫伍哪里不对\N{\rEng}What's he done to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.59,0:57:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,错在他们\N{\rEng}It's what they done!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.76,0:57:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我别无选择\N{\rEng}I got no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.49,0:57:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,谁都知道你不会伤害他  对吗\N{\rEng}You won't hurt Heywood. We all know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.00,0:57:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-对  我了解  -为何你不会伤害他\N{\rEng}-Right, Heywood?  -Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.70,0:57:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他是你朋友  而你明理\N{\rEng}He's a friend of yours, and Brooks is a reasonable man.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.30,0:58:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-有道理  对不对   -对\N{\rEng}-Right, guys? -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.34,0:58:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,老布  看着我  放下刀\N{\rEng}So put the knife down. Look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.11,0:58:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那就把刀放下\N{\rEng}Put the knife down.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.28,0:58:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,老布  你瞧他的脖子\N{\rEng}Look at his neck, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.11,0:58:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,他都流血了\N{\rEng}Look at his neck. He's bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.35,0:58:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,只有闯祸\N{\rEng}It's the only way
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.02,0:58:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,才能留在牢里\N{\rEng}they'd let me stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.35,0:58:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么会 别做傻事\N{\rEng}This is crazy.  You don't want to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.96,0:58:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,把刀放下吧\N{\rEng}Put it, put it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.80,0:58:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,放轻松一点\N{\rEng}Take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.97,0:58:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,不会有事的\N{\rEng}You'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.71,0:58:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他没事  我呢\N{\rEng}Him? What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.37,0:58:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,老疯狗差点割断我喉咙\N{\rEng}Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.98,0:58:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你刮胡子不也刀刀见血\N{\rEng}You've had worse from shaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.08,0:58:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎样惹毛他的\N{\rEng}What did you do to set him off?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.38,0:58:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,哪有  我只是来道别\N{\rEng}Nothing. I come in here to say farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.22,0:58:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,上面准他假释了\N{\rEng}Ain't you heard? His parole's come through.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.09,0:58:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我实在搞不明白\N{\rEng}I just don't understand what happened in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.23,0:58:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,老布抓狂得像起鸾\N{\rEng}Old man's crazy as a rat in a tin shithouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.23,0:59:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,赫伍  住口\N{\rEng}That's enough out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.33,0:59:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-听说你吓的屁滚尿流  -滚你的\N{\rEng}-Heard he had you shitting your pants. -Fuck you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.33,0:59:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,别斗嘴了\N{\rEng}IKnock it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.50,0:59:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,老布没疯\N{\rEng}Brooks ain't no bug.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.37,0:59:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他只是\N{\rEng}he is just
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.77,0:59:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,体制化了\N{\rEng}institutionalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.91,0:59:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,什么鸟词儿嘛\N{\rEng}"Institutionalized," my ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.05,0:59:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他坐了50年的牢  50年呀\N{\rEng}The man's been in here 50 years, Heywood, 50 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.25,0:59:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,成了井底之蛙\N{\rEng}This is all he knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.19,0:59:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他念过书\N{\rEng}In here, he's an important man
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.69,0:59:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,在狱中有地位\N{\rEng}an educated man.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.59,0:59:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,出狱就成了废人\N{\rEng}Outside, he's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.39,0:59:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,双手犯关节炎的囚徒\N{\rEng}Just a used-up con with arthritis in both hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.10,0:59:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,想向图书馆借书都会被拒\N{\rEng}Probably couldn't get a library card if he tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.37,0:59:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这样说你懂吗\N{\rEng}You know what I'm trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.37,0:59:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我才不懂你的满嘴屁话\N{\rEng}I do believe you're talking out of your ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.54,0:59:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,随你怎么说\N{\rEng}You believe whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.38,0:59:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,监狱是怪地方\N{\rEng}But I tell you these walls are funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.38,0:59:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,起先你恨它\N{\rEng}First you hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.88,0:59:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,然后习惯它\N{\rEng}Then you get used to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.72,0:59:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,更久后\N{\rEng}Enough time passes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.39,1:00:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能没有它\N{\rEng}you get so you depend on them.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.39,1:00:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,这就叫体制化\N{\rEng}That's "institutionalized."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.80,1:00:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,狗屎\N{\rEng}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.30,1:00:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-我才不会呢  -是吗\N{\rEng}-I could never get like that. -Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.93,1:00:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,等你50周年庆再说\N{\rEng}Wait till you've been here as long as Brooks.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.67,1:00:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这样\N{\rEng}Goddamn right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.81,1:00:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,判了无期徒刑\N{\rEng}They send you here for life
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.41,1:00:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,等于交出一生\N{\rEng}that's exactly what they take.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.48,1:00:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,至少得交出一部份\N{\rEng}Part that counts, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.09,1:00:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,小杰  我无法再照顾你\N{\rEng}I can't take care of you no more, Jake.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.19,1:00:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧  你自由了\N{\rEng}You go on now.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.10,1:00:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,自由了\N{\rEng}You're free.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.87,1:00:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,自由了\N{\rEng}You're free.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.45,1:01:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,一切顺利  老布\N{\rEng}Good luck, Brooksie.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.09,1:01:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,亲爱的牢友\N{\rEng}Dear fellas:
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.86,1:01:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,外头的变化快的难以置信\N{\rEng}I can't believe how fast things move on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.37,1:01:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,老头子  嫌命长呀\N{\rEng}Watch it, old-timer! Want to get killed?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.27,1:01:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,小时候我只看过一辆汽车\N{\rEng}I saw an automobile once when I was a kid
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.41,1:02:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,如今满街都是\N{\rEng}but now they're everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.52,1:02:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,整个世界忙成一团\N{\rEng}The world went and got itself in a big damn hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.64,1:02:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,上面安排我\N{\rEng}The parole board got me into this halfway house
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.71,1:02:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,在中途之家住\N{\rEng}called "The Brewer"
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.57,1:02:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,并在超市\N{\rEng}and a job
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.94,1:02:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,当包装员\N{\rEng}bagging groceries at the Food-Way.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.45,1:02:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,工作辛苦  我很努力\N{\rEng}It's hard work and I try to keep up
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.08,1:02:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,但双手一直犯疼\N{\rEng}..but my hands hurt most of the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.75,1:02:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,叫他务必用双层袋\N{\rEng}Make sure your man double-bags.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.92,1:02:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,上次差点撑破袋子\N{\rEng}Last time, the bottom near came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.62,1:02:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,确定要用双层袋\N{\rEng}Make sure you double-bag like the lady says. understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.76,1:02:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,是  没问题\N{\rEng}Yes, sir. Surely will.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.33,1:02:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,店长不怎么喜欢我\N{\rEng}I don't think the store manager likes me very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.87,1:03:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,下工后我去公园喂鸟\N{\rEng}Sometimes after work, I go to the park and feed the birds.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.61,1:03:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,盼望\N{\rEng}I keep thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.34,1:03:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,小杰来打个招呼\N{\rEng}Jake might just show up and say hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.28,1:03:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,但他没出现过\N{\rEng}But he never does.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.48,1:03:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,不管他在何处  我祝他过的好  有新朋友\N{\rEng}I hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay and making new friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.96,1:03:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我夜间难以入眠\N{\rEng}I have trouble sleeping at night.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.99,1:03:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,做着从高处坠落的恶梦\N{\rEng}I have bad dreams like I'm falling.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.53,1:03:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,醒时恐惧莫名\N{\rEng}I wake up scared.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.97,1:03:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,有时记不起身在何方\N{\rEng}Sometimes it takes me a while to remember where I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.71,1:03:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,也许我该持枪抢劫\N{\rEng}Maybe I should get a gun and rob the Food-Way so they'd send me home.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.91,1:03:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,毙了店长  重回肖申克  杀了他锦上添花\N{\rEng}I could shoot the manager while I was at it. Sort of like a bonus.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.92,1:03:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我老得无法再胡闹了\N{\rEng}I guess I'm too old for that sort of nonsense anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.15,1:03:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢这里\N{\rEng}I don't like it here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.09,1:03:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我厌倦成天担惊受怕\N{\rEng}I'm tired of being afraid all the time. I've decided
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.93,1:03:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,于是  我决心不再逗留\N{\rEng}not to stay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.51,1:04:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,当局不会在乎我\N{\rEng}I doubt they'll kick up any fuss
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.28,1:04:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,一个糟老头算什么\N{\rEng}not for an old crook like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.35,1:05:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}老布到此一游
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.24,1:05:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"当局不会在乎我  一个糟老头算什么\N{\rEng}"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss, not for an old crook like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.55,1:05:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,替我向赫伍道歉\N{\rEng}P.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry I put a knife to his throat.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.58,1:05:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,别记恨在心"\N{\rEng}No hard feelings. Brooks."
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.40,1:05:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,他还不如老死在肖申克好\N{\rEng}He should have died in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.90,1:05:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你在干什么\N{\rEng}What the fuck have you done?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.51,1:05:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,一片混乱\N{\rEng}It's a goddamn mess, I'll tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.71,1:06:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,-这些是什么   -你说呢  全是寄给你的\N{\rEng}-What's all this?  -You tell me. They're addressed to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.72,1:06:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你看\N{\rEng}Take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.60,1:06:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"杜弗伦先生\N{\rEng}"Dear Mr. Dufresne:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.23,1:06:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,鉴于你一再询问\N{\rEng}In response to your inquiries
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.40,1:06:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,本州特拨款给贵图书馆"\N{\rEng}the state has allocated the enclosed funds for your library project."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.44,1:06:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,金额两百元\N{\rEng}This is $ 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.47,1:06:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"另外  主管单位\N{\rEng}"In addition, the library district has generously responded
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.68,1:06:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,特地捐赠旧书及杂物\N{\rEng}with a donation of used books and sundries.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.45,1:06:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,相信可满足阁下需要  就此结案\N{\rEng}We trust this will fill your needs. We now consider the matter closed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.79,1:06:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,请勿再来信"\N{\rEng}Please stop sending us letters."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.82,1:06:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,典狱长回来前清干净\N{\rEng}Clear all this out before the warden gets back.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.72,1:06:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.16,1:06:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,干的好  安迪\N{\rEng}Good for you, Andy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.30,1:06:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,哇\N{\rEng}Wow!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.64,1:06:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,只写了六年\N{\rEng}It only took six years.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.14,1:06:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,现在起我一周两信\N{\rEng}From now on, I'll write two letters a week instead of one.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.08,1:07:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你真够固执的  听队长的话\N{\rEng}I believe you're crazy enough.  Get this stuff out
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.68,1:07:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,把东西清干净  我去撇大条\N{\rEng}like he said.I've got to pinch a loaf.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.32,1:07:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,别让我出来\N{\rEng}When I come back
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.98,1:07:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,再看到这些\N{\rEng}this is all gone, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.61,1:07:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}贾各头漫画
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.50,1:07:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪  什么声音\N{\rEng}Do you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.64,1:09:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,杜弗伦\N{\rEng}Dufresne!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.34,1:09:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪  放我出去\N{\rEng}Andy, let me out!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.85,1:09:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪\N{\rEng}Andy
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.75,1:09:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我从未搞懂她们唱什么\N{\rEng}I have no idea to this day what those two Italian ladies were singing about.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.99,1:09:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,其实我也不想弄懂\N{\rEng}Truth is, I don't want to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.42,1:09:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,此时无言胜有言\N{\rEng}Some things are best left unsaid.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.50,1:09:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,她们唱出\N{\rEng}I like to think it was something so beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.43,1:09:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,难以言传的美\N{\rEng}it can't be expressed in words
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.77,1:09:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,美的令你心碎\N{\rEng}and makes your heart ache because of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.34,1:09:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,歌声直窜云端\N{\rEng}I tell you, those voices soared
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.11,1:09:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,超越失意囚徒的梦想\N{\rEng}higher and farther than anybody in a gray place dares to dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.61,1:09:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,宛如小鸟飞入牢房\N{\rEng}It was like a beautiful bird flapped into our drab cage
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.18,1:09:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,使石墙消失无踪\N{\rEng}and made those walls dissolve away.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.39,1:10:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,就在这一瞬间\N{\rEng}And for the briefest of moments
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.79,1:10:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,肖申克众囚仿佛重获自由\N{\rEng}every last man at Shawshank felt free.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.36,1:10:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,典狱长可发飚了\N{\rEng}It pissed the warden off something awful.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.33,1:10:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,开门\N{\rEng}Open the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.24,1:10:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,开门呀\N{\rEng}Open it up!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.31,1:10:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,杜弗伦  开门\N{\rEng}Dufresne, open this door!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.38,1:10:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,关掉\N{\rEng}Turn that off!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.65,1:10:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我警告你  关掉\N{\rEng}I am warning you. Turn that off!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.20,1:10:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,杜弗伦\N{\rEng}Dufresne
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.84,1:10:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,敬酒不吃吃罚酒\N{\rEng}You're mine now.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.81,1:11:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪被罚囚两周\N{\rEng}Andy got two weeks in the hole for that little stunt.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.25,1:11:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,站起来\N{\rEng}On your feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.02,1:11:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-看谁来了  -大指挥家\N{\rEng}-Hey, look who's here.  -Maestro!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.19,1:11:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你没别的可放吗   比如汉克·威廉斯的歌\N{\rEng}You couldn't play something good, huh? Like Hank Williams?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.20,1:11:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,来不及接受点歌就被逮了\N{\rEng}They broke the door down before I could take requests.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.20,1:11:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,-关两周值得吗   -我最舒服的两周\N{\rEng}-Was it worth two weeks?  -Easiest time I ever did.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.54,1:11:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-屁话  独囚最难熬了  -在里面度日如年呀\N{\rEng}-No such thing as easy time in the hole. -A week in the hole is like a year.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.94,1:11:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,-最难熬了  -有莫扎特陪我\N{\rEng}-Damn straight.  -I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.44,1:11:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他们准你带电唱机\N{\rEng}So they let you tote that record player down there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.85,1:11:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,在脑中\N{\rEng}It was in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.05,1:11:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,在心底\N{\rEng}In here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.42,1:11:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,音乐之美\N{\rEng}That's the beauty of music. They
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.72,1:11:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,是夺不走的\N{\rEng}can't get that from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.59,1:11:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你没体会过吗\N{\rEng}Haven't you ever felt that way about music?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.77,1:11:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我年轻时吹口琴\N{\rEng}Well, I played a mean harmonica as a younger man.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.94,1:11:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,没兴致了\N{\rEng}Lost interest in it, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.84,1:11:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,在牢里也没意义\N{\rEng}Didn't make much sense in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.77,1:11:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,就是在这里才有意义\N{\rEng}Here's where it makes the most sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.31,1:12:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,有音乐才不会忘记\N{\rEng}You need it so you don't forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.95,1:12:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,忘记什么\N{\rEng}Forget?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.51,1:12:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,这个世上\N{\rEng}Forget that there are
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.82,1:12:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,有些地方\N{\rEng}places
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.75,1:12:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,是石墙关不住的\N{\rEng}in the world that aren't made out of stone.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.59,1:12:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,在人的\N{\rEng}There's something
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.43,1:12:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,内心\N{\rEng}inside
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.09,1:12:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,有他们\N{\rEng}that they can't get to
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.26,1:12:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,管不到的东西\N{\rEng}that they can't touch.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.16,1:12:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,是完全属于你的\N{\rEng}That's yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.13,1:12:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你指什么\N{\rEng}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.77,1:12:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,希望\N{\rEng}Hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.07,1:12:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,希望\N{\rEng}Hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.34,1:12:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,朋友  我告诉你\N{\rEng}Let me tell you something, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.15,1:12:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,有希望才危险\N{\rEng}Hope is a dangerous thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.62,1:12:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,希望能把人弄疯\N{\rEng}Hope can drive a man insane.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.68,1:12:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,希望无用\N{\rEng}It's got no use on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.02,1:12:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你最好认命\N{\rEng}You'd better get used to that idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.73,1:12:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,要像老布一样吗\N{\rEng}Like Brooks did?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.59,1:13:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,坐下\N{\rEng}Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.93,1:13:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你判无期徒刑  已经30年\N{\rEng}Says here that you've served 30 years of a life sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.40,1:13:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你改过自新了吗\N{\rEng}You feel you've been rehabilitated?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.67,1:13:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  确实如此\N{\rEng}Oh, yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.17,1:13:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我真的已经变好\N{\rEng}Without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.67,1:13:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我完全洗心革面了\N{\rEng}I can honestly say I'm a changed man.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.07,1:13:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会危害社会\N{\rEng}No danger to society here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.54,1:13:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,上帝为证\N{\rEng}God's honest truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.65,1:13:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,完全洗心革面了\N{\rEng}Absolutely rehabilitated.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.85,1:13:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}驳回
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.79,1:13:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,30年了\N{\rEng}Thirty years.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.10,1:14:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,老天  真不知该说什么\N{\rEng}Jesus, when you say it like that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.87,1:14:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,这些日子怎么熬过来的\N{\rEng}You wonder where it went.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.10,1:14:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我连前十年都不记得\N{\rEng}I wonder where 10 years went.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.24,1:14:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,拿去\N{\rEng}Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.71,1:14:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,假释被拒的礼物\N{\rEng}A little parole rejection present.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.72,1:14:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,打开看看\N{\rEng}Go ahead and open it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.52,1:14:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,别介意我找你同行买\N{\rEng}Went through one of your competitors.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.75,1:14:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我只想让你惊喜\N{\rEng}I hope you don't mind. I wanted it to be a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.93,1:14:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,漂亮极了\N{\rEng}It's very pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.14,1:14:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.91,1:14:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你不吹吗\N{\rEng}You going to play it?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.95,1:14:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.82,1:14:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,不是时候\N{\rEng}Not right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.90,1:15:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,进房\N{\rEng}Roll in!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.87,1:15:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}十周年庆  瑞德赠
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.21,1:15:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,熄灯\N{\rEng}Lights out!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.04,1:16:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪言出必行\N{\rEng}Andy was as good as his word.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.55,1:16:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,每周写两封信\N{\rEng}He wrote two letters a week instead of one.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.39,1:16:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,59年  州议会终于明白\N{\rEng}In 1959, the state senate finally clued in to the fact
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.72,1:16:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,两百元无法打发安迪\N{\rEng}they couldn't buy him off with just a $ 200 check.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.06,1:16:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,当局决议每年付五百元\N{\rEng}Appropriations Committee voted an annual payment of $500
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.56,1:16:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,好让安迪封笔\N{\rEng}just to shut him up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.67,1:16:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你想像不到他的能耐\N{\rEng}And you'd be amazed how far Andy could stretch it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.87,1:16:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他接洽读书会  慈善团体\N{\rEng}He made deals with book clubs, charity groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.01,1:16:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他论斤买入旧书\N{\rEng}He bought remaindered books by the pound
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.28,1:17:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,金银岛\N{\rEng}Treasure Island.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.34,1:17:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,罗伯特·路易斯\N{\rEng}Robert Louis
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.88,1:17:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,史帝文森\N{\rEng}Stevenson.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.11,1:17:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,冒险小说类\N{\rEng}Fiction, adventure.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.05,1:17:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,再来呢\N{\rEng}What's next?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.29,1:17:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,汽车修护\N{\rEng}I got here Auto Repair
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.09,1:17:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,肥皂雕刻\N{\rEng}and Soap Carving.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.46,1:17:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,专业技术及嗜好  教育类  在你后面\N{\rEng}Trade skills and hobbies. Under "Educational," behind you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.89,1:17:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,基基山恩仇记\N{\rEng}Count of Monte Crisco.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.23,1:17:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,基督山啦  饭桶\N{\rEng}That's "Cristo," you dumb shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.63,1:17:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,作者亚历山大\N{\rEng}By Alexandree
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.10,1:17:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,大种马\N{\rEng}Dum-ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.70,1:17:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,种马\N{\rEng}Dumb ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.04,1:17:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,种马\N{\rEng}Dumb ass?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.01,1:17:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,大仲马  内容知道吗\N{\rEng}Dumas. IKnow what that's about?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.25,1:17:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,讲越狱  你会喜欢\N{\rEng}You'd like it. It's about a prison break.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.42,1:17:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,那该归入教育类喽\N{\rEng}We ought to file that under "Educational" too, oughtn't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.19,1:17:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,大伙儿尽可能帮安迪\N{\rEng}The rest of us did our best to pitch in when and where we could.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.86,1:17:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在肯尼迪遇刺之前\N{\rEng}By the year Kennedy was shot
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.86,1:17:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪把这臭储藏室变成\N{\rEng}Andy had transformed a storage room smelling of turpentine
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.67,1:18:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,新英格兰最棒的监狱图书馆\N{\rEng}into the best prison library in New England
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.47,1:18:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至有汉克·威廉斯精选集\N{\rEng}complete with a fine selection of Hank Williams.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.78,1:18:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,就在同年\N{\rEng}That was also when Warden Norton
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.92,1:18:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,典狱长实施著名的外役专案\N{\rEng}instituted his famous "Inside Out" program.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.32,1:18:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,也许你曾在报上看过\N{\rEng}You may remember reading about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.62,1:18:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他上了各报和《展望杂志》\N{\rEng}It made the papers and got his picture in Look magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.92,1:18:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,这不只是赚钱\N{\rEng}It's no free ride
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.43,1:18:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,而是狱政的\N{\rEng}but rather a genuine progressive advance
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.86,1:18:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,一大进步\N{\rEng}in corrections and rehabilitation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.70,1:18:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,本监受刑人在妥善监督下\N{\rEng}Our inmates, properly supervised
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.44,1:18:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,将到狱外工作\N{\rEng}will be put to work outside these walls
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.27,1:18:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,从事各项公共事业\N{\rEng}performing all manner of public service.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.54,1:18:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他们将学到诚实劳动的价值\N{\rEng}These men can learn the value
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.54,1:18:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,同时为社区提供服务\N{\rEng}of an honest day's labor and provide a service to the community
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.55,1:18:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,对于纳税大众而言  也只花最少的代价\N{\rEng}at a bare minimum of expense to Mr. And Mrs. John Q. Taxpayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.69,1:18:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,当然  诺顿没向媒体说明\N{\rEng}Of course he didn't tell the press
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.22,1:18:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"最少代价"实在含糊不清\N{\rEng}that "bare minimum of expense" is a fairly loose term.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.89,1:19:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,揩油的方法何止百种\N{\rEng}There are 100 different ways to skim off the top.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.13,1:19:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,人力  物料  处处漏洞\N{\rEng}Men, materials, you name it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.97,1:19:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,天哪  油水之丰\N{\rEng}And oh, my Lord, how the money rolled in!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.07,1:19:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你会害我倒闭的\N{\rEng}At this rate, you'll put me out of business.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.80,1:19:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,靠这么多奴工  谁标得过你\N{\rEng}With this pool of slave labor, you can underbid any contractor in town.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.81,1:19:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在提供社区服务\N{\rEng}We're providing a valuable community service.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.98,1:19:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,这是广告词  但我得养家  山姆\N{\rEng}That's fine for the papers, but I've got a family to feed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.32,1:19:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,老兄  咱们这么久的交情\N{\rEng}We go back a long way.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.16,1:19:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须包下这条公路  否则只好喝西北风了\N{\rEng}I need this highway contract. I don't get it and I go under. That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.99,1:19:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这是内人特地为你烤的派\N{\rEng}You have some of this fine pie
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.03,1:19:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,请笑纳  你看着办\N{\rEng}my missus made for you. You think about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.64,1:19:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,别担心这项工程合约\N{\rEng}I wouldn't worry too much about this contract.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.58,1:19:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我已叫他们接别的案子了\N{\rEng}I already got my boys committed elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.62,1:19:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,帮我谢谢她的心意\N{\rEng}You be sure and thank Maisie for this fine pie.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.79,1:20:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,在每一桩买卖后面\N{\rEng}And behind every shady deal
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.29,1:20:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,在每一元黑钱底下\N{\rEng}behind every dollar earned
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.19,1:20:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,都有安迪在  是他做的帐\N{\rEng}there was Andy, keeping the books.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.66,1:20:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,您有两笔款要存入银行\N{\rEng}Two deposits.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.16,1:20:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,照旧在夜间  存到常来往的银行\N{\rEng}Maine National and New England First. Night drops as always, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.50,1:20:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,把东西拿去洗衣房  两套西装和杂物\N{\rEng}Get my stuff to the laundry. Two suits for dry-clean and a bag of whatnot.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.30,1:20:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-别搞太硬  否则有他们好看  -是的  先生\N{\rEng}-If they over-starch my shirts again, they'll hear from me.-Yes Sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.04,1:20:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎样\N{\rEng}How do I look?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.41,1:20:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,-很好  先生  -我去慈善宴会\N{\rEng}-Very nice.  -Big charity to-do up Portland way.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.10,1:20:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,州长会到\N{\rEng}Governor will be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.05,1:21:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,剩下的给你吃\N{\rEng}You want the rest of this?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.85,1:21:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,烤的难吃透顶\N{\rEng}Woman can't bake worth shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.02,1:21:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢您  先生\N{\rEng}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.19,1:21:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-这种派他收过很多  -你听说的只是皮毛\N{\rEng}He's got his fingers in a lot of pies, from what I hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.63,1:21:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他干的坏事你想不到  重重的回扣\N{\rEng}He's got scams you haven't even dreamed of. IKickbacks on his kickbacks.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.67,1:21:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,黑钱如河般在他脚下流\N{\rEng}A river of dirty money running through here.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.24,1:21:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,贪污这么多迟早会曝光\N{\rEng}Sooner or later, he'll have to explain where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.27,1:21:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,因此才要用我\N{\rEng}That's where I come in.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.64,1:21:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我过滤黑钱  一一漂白\N{\rEng}I channel it. Filter it. Funnel it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.15,1:21:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,股票  证券  市政公债\N{\rEng}Stocks, securities, tax-free municipals.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.31,1:21:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我让脏钱流入市场  等它回流时\N{\rEng}I send it out into the real world, and when it comes back
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.05,1:21:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-干净的像处女   -比那更干净\N{\rEng}-Clean as a virgin's honeypot, huh?  -Cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.62,1:21:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,诺顿退休时  将是百万富翁\N{\rEng}By the time Norton retires, I'll have made him a millionaire.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.56,1:21:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,若被逮到  他也会被关入肖申克\N{\rEng}If they ever catch on, he'll wind up in here wearing a number himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.17,1:21:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你对我这么没信心呀\N{\rEng}I thought you had more faith in me than that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.07,1:21:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我知道你很厉害  但文件会留下证据\N{\rEng}I know you're good, but all that paper leaves a trail.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.31,1:22:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,万一调查局或国税局起疑\N{\rEng}Now anybody gets curious, FBI, IRS
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.91,1:22:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,就完了\N{\rEng}whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.34,1:22:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,总有人要遭殃\N{\rEng}It'll lead to somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.85,1:22:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  但不是我  更不是典狱长\N{\rEng}Sure it is, but not to me, and certainly not to the warden.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.09,1:22:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,那是谁\N{\rEng}All right, who?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.29,1:22:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,兰德尔·史蒂文斯\N{\rEng}Randall Stevens.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.36,1:22:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,谁\N{\rEng}Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.56,1:22:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,隐名又隐形的合伙人\N{\rEng}The "silent" silent partner.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.76,1:22:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,法官  都怪他  户头是他的\N{\rEng}He's the guilty one, the man with the bank accounts.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.03,1:22:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,他是洗钱的起点\N{\rEng}It's where the filtering process starts.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.40,1:22:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,出了差错  只追得到他\N{\rEng}They trace anything, it'll just lead to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.87,1:22:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,但他是什么人\N{\rEng}But who is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.30,1:22:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,他是幻影  幽灵  兔宝宝的远房表亲\N{\rEng}He's a phantom, an apparition. Second cousin to Harvey the Rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.38,1:22:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我一手塑造他\N{\rEng}I conjured him
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.74,1:22:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,凭空的\N{\rEng}out of thin air.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.91,1:22:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,他不存在  除了在文件上\N{\rEng}He doesn't exist, except on paper.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.72,1:22:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,哪有凭空造人的\N{\rEng}You can't just make a person up.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.29,1:22:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,利用制度的漏洞就行\N{\rEng}Sure you can, if you know how the system works.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.89,1:22:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,靠写信能办成太多的事\N{\rEng}It's amazing what you can accomplish by mail.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.06,1:22:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂文斯有出生证明\N{\rEng}Mr. Stevens has a birth certificate
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.90,1:22:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,有驾照  社会保险编号\N{\rEng}driver's license, Social Security.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.30,1:22:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你没蒙我吧\N{\rEng}You're shitting me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.50,1:23:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,就算抓到蛛丝马迹\N{\rEng}If they trace any accounts, they'll wind up chasing
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.07,1:23:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是捕风捉影\N{\rEng}a figment of my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.01,1:23:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,真想不到\N{\rEng}Well, I'll be damned!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.34,1:23:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我有称赞过你吧\N{\rEng}Did I say you were good?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.45,1:23:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你简直是大艺术家\N{\rEng}Shit, you are Rembrandt.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.81,1:23:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,可笑的是\N{\rEng}The funny thing is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.75,1:23:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,在外头  我刚正不阿\N{\rEng}on the outside, I was an honest man, straight as an arrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.25,1:23:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,进了牢  却大搞歪哥\N{\rEng}I had to come to prison to be a crook.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.47,1:23:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你心安吗\N{\rEng}Ever bother you?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.20,1:23:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我没干坏事  只是洗钱\N{\rEng}I don't run the scams.I just process the profits.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.54,1:23:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,也许这是强词夺理\N{\rEng}A fine line, maybe
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.11,1:23:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但我只手成立图书馆\N{\rEng}but I also built that library
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.38,1:23:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,帮助囚友考取中学文凭\N{\rEng}and used it to help guys get their high school diploma.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.61,1:23:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,典狱长凭什么任我做\N{\rEng}Why do you think he lets me do all that?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.05,1:23:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,为了使你\N{\rEng}IKeep you happy and doing the laundry.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.45,1:23:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,乐于帮他洗钱\N{\rEng}Money instead of sheets.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.29,1:23:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我算是便宜卖给他\N{\rEng}Well, I work cheap. That's the tradeoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.14,1:24:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,汤米在65年来到肖申克\N{\rEng}Tommy Williams came to Shawshank in 1965
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.01,1:24:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,犯了"破闯"判了两年\N{\rEng}on a two-year stretch for B and E.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.48,1:24:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,就是强行入侵他人公宅\N{\rEng}That's breaking and entering to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.08,1:24:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,他在商店后门偷彩电时被逮\N{\rEng}Cops caught him sneaking TV sets out the back door of a JC Penney.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.75,1:24:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,小庞克\N{\rEng}Young punk.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.25,1:24:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,摇滚狂一个\N{\rEng}Mr. Rock 'n' Roll
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.09,1:24:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,跩得够可爱\N{\rEng}cocky as hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.82,1:24:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,快啦  各位老兄  慢吞吞的\N{\rEng}Come on, old boys. Moving like molasses!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.46,1:24:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我看了难过\N{\rEng}Making me look bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.43,1:24:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,人见人爱\N{\rEng}We liked him immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.46,1:24:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我退出门外  我这样抱着电视\N{\rEng}I'm backing out the door and I got the TV like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.50,1:24:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,它很大  害我看不见  忽然传出声音\N{\rEng}A big old thing. I couldn't see shit. Then I hear this voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.77,1:24:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"别动  手举起来"\N{\rEng}"Freeze, kid, hands in the air."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.94,1:24:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我站着抱紧电视\N{\rEng}I was standing there, holding onto that TV. Finally the voice says:
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.61,1:24:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他又说"你听没有 "  我说有  但我若松手\N{\rEng}"You hear what I said, boy?" I say, "Yes, sir. I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.62,1:24:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,就一条毁损财产罪\N{\rEng}But if I drop this, you get me on destruction of property too."
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.56,1:25:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你在凯希曼监狱蹲过\N{\rEng}You done some stretch in Cashman, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.36,1:25:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,那是最好混的日子\N{\rEng}Yeah, that was an easy piece of time, let me tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.60,1:25:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,周末回家  外役制度\N{\rEng}Weekend furloughs. Work programs.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.73,1:25:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,不像这里\N{\rEng}Not like here.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.00,1:25:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你哪里都蹲过嘛\N{\rEng}Sounds like you done time all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.87,1:25:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我13岁起以牢为家\N{\rEng}I've been in and out since I was 13.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.47,1:25:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你想的到的监狱我都待过\N{\rEng}Name it, chances are I've been there.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.88,1:25:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,也许你该改行了\N{\rEng}Perhaps you should try a new profession.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.98,1:25:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,依我看\N{\rEng}What I mean is
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.88,1:25:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你的贼功不灵光  该做做别的事\N{\rEng}you're not a very good thief.You should try something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.55,1:25:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你懂个屁  你是卡彭呀\N{\rEng}Yeah, what the hell you know about it, Capone?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.19,1:25:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你为何入狱\N{\rEng}What are you in for?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.06,1:25:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我\N{\rEng}Me?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.49,1:25:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,被律师害了\N{\rEng}A lawyer fucked me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.07,1:25:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,肖申克没人有罪  你不懂吗\N{\rEng}Everybody's innocent in here. Don't you know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.94,1:26:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,汤米有娇妻和一女儿\N{\rEng}As it turned out, Tommy had himself a young wife and a new baby girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.92,1:26:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他怕妻女流落街头\N{\rEng}Maybe he thought of them on the streets
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.25,1:26:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,不认识老爸\N{\rEng}or his child growing up not knowing her daddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.05,1:26:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,或是别的原因\N{\rEng}Whatever it was
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.76,1:26:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,反正这小子卯上了\N{\rEng}something lit a fire under that boy's ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.03,1:26:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我想考同等学历\N{\rEng}Thought I might try for my high school equivalency.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.10,1:26:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,听说你帮过人\N{\rEng}Hear you helped a couple of fellas with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.97,1:26:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我不帮废人\N{\rEng}I don't waste time with losers, Tommy.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.61,1:26:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我才不是废人\N{\rEng}I ain't no goddamn loser.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.84,1:26:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,-你有心   -对\N{\rEng}-You mean that?  -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.35,1:26:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,真的有心\N{\rEng}You really mean that?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.82,1:26:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  我有\N{\rEng}Yes, sir, I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.38,1:26:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,好  要冲就冲到底\N{\rEng}Good. Because if we do this
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.55,1:26:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,百分之百  不可退却\N{\rEng}we do it all the way, a hundred percent, nothing half-assed.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.76,1:26:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,问题是\N{\rEng}Thing is, see
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.83,1:26:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我不太识字\N{\rEng}I don't read so good.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.53,1:26:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"没关系"\N{\rEng}"Well."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.63,1:26:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你\N{\rEng}You don't read
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.60,1:26:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,不识字\N{\rEng}so well.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.47,1:26:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,交给我吧\N{\rEng}We'll get to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.41,1:27:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪收汤米为徒\N{\rEng}So Andy took Tommy under his wing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.75,1:27:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,从字母教起\N{\rEng}Started walking him through his ABC's.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.52,1:27:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,汤米学的非常好\N{\rEng}Tommy took to it pretty well too.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.99,1:27:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他从未发现自己有天份\N{\rEng}Boy found brains he never knew he had.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.09,1:27:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,没多久就始准备应试\N{\rEng}Before long, Andy started him on his course requirements.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.73,1:27:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪真心喜欢他\N{\rEng}He really liked the kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.60,1:27:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,助人向上令他兴奋\N{\rEng}Gave him a thrill to help a youngster crawl off the shit heap.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.67,1:27:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,但动机不止于此\N{\rEng}But that wasn't the only reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.64,1:27:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,牢狱生活缓慢得很\N{\rEng}Prison time is slow time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.31,1:27:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,必须找事打发时间\N{\rEng}So you do what you can to keep going.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.24,1:27:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,有人集邮\N{\rEng}Some fellas collect stamps.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.71,1:27:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,有人盖火柴屋\N{\rEng}Others build matchstick houses.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.78,1:27:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪成立了图书馆\N{\rEng}Andy built a library.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.95,1:27:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,如今他需要新计划\N{\rEng}Now he needed a new project.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.76,1:27:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,就是汤米\N{\rEng}Tommy was it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.89,1:27:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这跟他长年刻石一样\N{\rEng}It was the same reason he spent years shaping and polishing those rocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.43,1:27:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,也跟他挂美女图一样\N{\rEng}The same reason he hung his fantasy girlies on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.57,1:27:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,在牢里\N{\rEng}In prison
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.10,1:28:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,没事也得找事做\N{\rEng}a man will do most anything to keep his mind occupied.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.61,1:28:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,1966年  就在汤米应考之前\N{\rEng}By 1966, right about the time Tommy was getting ready to take his exams
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.71,1:28:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,换上拉寇儿·薇芝了\N{\rEng}it was lovely Raquel.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.46,1:28:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,时间到\N{\rEng}Time.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.50,1:28:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,怎样\N{\rEng}Well?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.11,1:28:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,烂透了\N{\rEng}Well, it's for shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.74,1:28:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我他妈白费一整年\N{\rEng}I wasted a whole year of my time with this bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.78,1:28:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,也许没那么糟\N{\rEng}It's probably not that bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.48,1:28:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,更糟啦  没一题做对  简直像中文一样看不懂\N{\rEng}I didn't get a thing right.It might as well have been in Chinese.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.92,1:28:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,分数出来再说\N{\rEng}Let's see how the score comes out.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.85,1:28:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我告诉你几分吧\N{\rEng}I'll tell you how the goddamn score comes out.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.76,1:28:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,两分入网\N{\rEng}Two points, right there!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.33,1:28:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是分数\N{\rEng}There's your goddamn score!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.13,1:29:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,什么猫爬树  五五二十五\N{\rEng}Goddamn cats crawling up trees,5 times 5 is 25
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.77,1:29:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,去他妈的蛋\N{\rEng}Fuck this place!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.63,1:29:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,去他妈的\N{\rEng}Fuck it!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.92,1:29:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,真后悔\N{\rEng}I feel bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.39,1:29:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,让他失望\N{\rEng}I let him down.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.79,1:29:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,胡说\N{\rEng}That's crap, kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.73,1:29:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,他以你为荣\N{\rEng}He's proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.39,1:29:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,多年的交情  我摸透他了\N{\rEng}We're old friends,I know him as good as anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.46,1:29:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,他是聪明人\N{\rEng}Smart fellow, ain't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.23,1:29:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,绝顶聪明  曾是银行家\N{\rEng}Smart as they come. He was a banker on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.57,1:29:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他究竟为何入狱\N{\rEng}What's he in here for anyway?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.11,1:29:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,谋杀\N{\rEng}Murder.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.57,1:29:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你少扯了\N{\rEng}The hell, you say.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.08,1:29:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,看他外表是想不到\N{\rEng}You wouldn't think it to look at the guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.65,1:29:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,捉到老婆跟高球教练在床  两个全干了\N{\rEng}Caught his wife in bed with some golf pro. Greased them both.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.76,1:30:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.10,1:30:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,大约四年前\N{\rEng}About four years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.93,1:30:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我在托马斯顿监狱服刑\N{\rEng}I was in Thomaston on a two-to-three stretch.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.67,1:30:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我偷了车\N{\rEng}I stole a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.34,1:30:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,实在愚蠢\N{\rEng}It was a dumb-fuck thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.01,1:30:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,剩下半年时\N{\rEng}About six months left to go
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.54,1:30:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,来了新室友\N{\rEng}I get a new cellmate in.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.15,1:30:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,名叫厄摩\N{\rEng}Elmo Blatch.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.48,1:30:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,大个子  紧张狂\N{\rEng}Big, twitchy fucker.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.68,1:30:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,谁都怕碰上这种室友\N{\rEng}IKind of roomie you pray you don't get. You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.39,1:30:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,入室行窃  服刑6至12年\N{\rEng}Six-to-twelve, armed burglary.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.39,1:30:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他说他干过好几百票\N{\rEng}Said he pulled hundreds of jobs.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.86,1:30:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,想不到有那么神经的人  闻到屁味也跳到半天高\N{\rEng}Hard to believe, high-strung as he was.You cut a loud fart, he jumped three feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.86,1:30:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他的嘴永远闭不上\N{\rEng}Talked all the time too. That's the other thing. He never shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.70,1:30:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,他去过的地方\N{\rEng}Places he'd been in
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.64,1:30:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,犯的罪  玩过的女人\N{\rEng}jobs he'd pulled, women he fucked.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.94,1:30:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至杀过的人\N{\rEng}Even people he killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.38,1:31:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他说杀人\N{\rEng}People who "gave him shit."
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.82,1:31:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为不爽\N{\rEng}That's how he put it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.68,1:31:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,有一晚  我半开玩笑\N{\rEng}So one night, like a joke
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.16,1:31:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我问他"你杀过谁 "\N{\rEng}I say to him,"Elmo, who did you kill?"
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.89,1:31:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,他说\N{\rEng}So he says:
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.19,1:31:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我在俱乐部收盘子\N{\rEng}I got me this job one time,busing tables at a country club
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.83,1:31:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,趁机观察阔人下手\N{\rEng}so I could case all these bigrich pricks that come in.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.84,1:31:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我相中一人\N{\rEng}So I pick out this guy
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.74,1:31:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,在晚上\N{\rEng}go in one night
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.51,1:31:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,摸进他家\N{\rEng}and do his place.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.68,1:31:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他醒来\N{\rEng}He wakes up
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.75,1:31:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,惹的我不爽\N{\rEng}and gives me shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.58,1:31:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我就宰了他\N{\rEng}So I killed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.02,1:31:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,和他身边那骚货\N{\rEng}Him and this tasty bitch he was with.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.26,1:31:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,精彩的是\N{\rEng}And that's the best part.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.19,1:31:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,她搞上高球教练\N{\rEng}She's fucking this prick, see
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.86,1:31:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,家有老公  却跟别的男人搞在一起\N{\rEng}this golf pro,but she's married to some other guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.53,1:31:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,一个大银行家\N{\rEng}Some hotshot banker.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.54,1:32:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,却成了代罪羔羊\N{\rEng}And he's the one they pinned it on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.52,1:32:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我从未听过如此惊人的故事\N{\rEng}I have to say that's the most amazing story I ever heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.66,1:32:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,最惊人的是你居然受骗\N{\rEng}What amazes me most is you'd be taken in by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.89,1:32:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rEng}Sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.10,1:32:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,显然汤米对你颇有好感\N{\rEng}It's obvious this fellow Williams is impressed with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.30,1:32:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,知道你痛苦  自然想让你高兴\N{\rEng}He hears your tale of woe and naturally wants to cheer you up.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.44,1:32:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他还小  脑筋不太灵光\N{\rEng}He's young, not terribly bright.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.14,1:32:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,根本不明白会害苦了你\N{\rEng}It's not surprising he wouldn't know what a state he put you in.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.98,1:32:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他说的是实情\N{\rEng}Sir, he's telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.31,1:32:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,就算真有厄摩这人\N{\rEng}Let's say for the moment this Blatch does exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.75,1:32:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,难道他会跪地哭诉  "是我杀的  我忏悔"\N{\rEng}You think he'd just fall to his knees and cry, "Yes, I did it. I confess.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.59,1:32:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"顺便给我加个无期徒刑"\N{\rEng}By the way, add a life term to my sentence."
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.49,1:32:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,有汤米做证  我可重审\N{\rEng}With Tommy's testimony,I can get a new trial.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.50,1:32:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,但你得找到厄摩\N{\rEng}That's assuming Blatch is still there.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.20,1:33:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,他可能早就出狱了\N{\rEng}Chances are, he'd be released by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.33,1:33:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,但能查到住址和亲友  这是机会呀\N{\rEng}They'd have his last known address.It's a chance, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.27,1:33:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是个阿呆\N{\rEng}How can you be so obtuse?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.94,1:33:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.45,1:33:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你说我什么\N{\rEng}What did you call me?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.12,1:33:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你笨蛋  我说错了吗\N{\rEng}Obtuse. Is it deliberate?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.22,1:33:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你别忘了身份\N{\rEng}You're forgetting yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.05,1:33:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,俱乐部有厄摩的资料\N{\rEng}The country club will have his old timecards.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.19,1:33:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,还有记录  税单\N{\rEng}Records, W-2s with his name on them.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.16,1:33:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你爱幻想  那是你的事\N{\rEng}If you want to indulge this fantasy,it's your business.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.06,1:33:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,别给我添麻烦  面谈结束\N{\rEng}Don't make it mine.This meeting is over.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.86,1:33:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我若出狱  绝不提你的事\N{\rEng}If I got out, I'd never mentionwhat happens here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.10,1:33:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我洗钱  与你同罪\N{\rEng}I'd be as indictable as you for laundering that money.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.10,1:33:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不许你说钱这个字  兔崽子\N{\rEng}Don't ever mention money to me,you son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.08,1:33:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,到哪里\N{\rEng}Not in this office
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.94,1:33:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,都不许说  进来\N{\rEng}not anywhere.Get in here, now!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.11,1:33:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我只想让你安心\N{\rEng}I just wanted to put you at ease,that's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.45,1:33:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-独囚一个月  -是的\N{\rEng}-Solitary. A month. -Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.72,1:33:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-你是怎么搞的   -带走\N{\rEng}-what's wrong with you? -Get him out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.72,1:33:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我重获自由的机会  你不懂吗   这是我的人生\N{\rEng}This is my chance to get out! It's my life! Understand?!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.49,1:33:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,带出去\N{\rEng}Get him out!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.33,1:34:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,独囚一个月\N{\rEng}A month in the hole.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.50,1:34:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,没听过这么久的处罚\N{\rEng}That's the longest stretch I ever heard of.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.40,1:34:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,都是我不对\N{\rEng}It's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.90,1:34:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,胡说八道\N{\rEng}Bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.17,1:34:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你没杀人  也没判安迪的罪\N{\rEng}You didn't pull the trigger or convict him.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.07,1:34:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说安迪没罪\N{\rEng}Are you saying Andy is innocent?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.68,1:34:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他真的无辜\N{\rEng}I mean, for real innocent?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.91,1:34:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,看来是这样\N{\rEng}It looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.68,1:34:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我的天呀\N{\rEng}Sweet Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.85,1:34:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他服刑多久了\N{\rEng}How long has he been here now?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.08,1:34:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,47年进来  19年了\N{\rEng}1947. What is that? Nineteen years.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.59,1:34:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,-汤米的信  -在这里\N{\rEng}-Williams, Thomas.  -Yeah, over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.03,1:34:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,是什么\N{\rEng}What you got?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.83,1:34:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,教育委员会来的\N{\rEng}Board of Education.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.37,1:34:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,老小子寄出那考卷了\N{\rEng}That son of a bitch mailed it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.10,1:34:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-没错  -你要拆  或是拿着傻看\N{\rEng}You going to open it or stand there with your thumb up your butt?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.27,1:34:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,拿着看好些\N{\rEng}Thumb up my butt sounds better.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.94,1:34:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,拿来啦  痞子\N{\rEng}Skeets, come on.Give me that, you shithead.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.61,1:34:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,福洛\N{\rEng}Floyd, come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.75,1:34:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德\N{\rEng}Red
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.39,1:35:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,把它丢掉  好吗\N{\rEng}Will you throw that away, please?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.39,1:35:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,真不错\N{\rEng}Well, shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.81,1:35:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他考取了  平均丙上\N{\rEng}The kid passed. C + average.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.81,1:35:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,跟你报个喜\N{\rEng}Thought you'd like to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.13,1:35:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,典狱长找你谈话\N{\rEng}Warden wants to talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.34,1:35:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在这儿\N{\rEng}Out here?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.61,1:36:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,他是这样说的\N{\rEng}That's what the man said.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.96,1:36:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,典狱长\N{\rEng}Warden?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.90,1:36:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,汤米\N{\rEng}Tommy
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.34,1:36:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,汤米  这次会面要你守密\N{\rEng}Tommy, I'm asking you to keep this conversation just between us.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.55,1:36:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我良心深感不安\N{\rEng}I feel awkward enough as it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.27,1:36:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,他的判决出了问题\N{\rEng}We got a situation here.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.20,1:36:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你明白\N{\rEng}I think you can appreciate that.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.51,1:37:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.01,1:37:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我明白\N{\rEng}I sure can.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.68,1:37:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这件事真的使我震惊\N{\rEng}I tell you, son, this thing really came along and knocked my wind out.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.18,1:37:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我连觉都睡不好\N{\rEng}It's got me up nights.That's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.02,1:37:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我该怎么做才好\N{\rEng}The right thing to do
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.52,1:37:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,有时连我也不清楚\N{\rEng}sometimes it's hard to know what that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.26,1:37:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你了解吗\N{\rEng}Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.00,1:37:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我需要你的协助\N{\rEng}I need your help, son.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.04,1:37:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我要有\N{\rEng}If I'm going to move on this
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.54,1:37:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,十足把握才能翻案\N{\rEng}there can't be the least little shred of doubt.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.44,1:37:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我得知道\N{\rEng}I have to know
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.71,1:37:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你是否说实话\N{\rEng}if what you told Dufresne was the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.55,1:37:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.88,1:37:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,字字属实\N{\rEng}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.62,1:37:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你愿在法官及陪审团前宣誓\N{\rEng}Would you be willing to swear before a judge and jury
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.82,1:37:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,并且手按圣经\N{\rEng}with your hand on the Good Book
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.02,1:37:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在上主跟前起誓\N{\rEng}and take an oath before Almighty God himself?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.89,1:37:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我绝不迟疑\N{\rEng}Just give me that chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.96,1:37:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我也是这样想\N{\rEng}That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.38,1:38:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,相信你已听说了\N{\rEng}I'm sure by now you've heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.05,1:38:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,真惨\N{\rEng}Terrible thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.68,1:38:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,英年早逝\N{\rEng}A man that young
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.49,1:38:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,剩不到一年还要逃\N{\rEng}less than a year to go, trying to escape.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.62,1:38:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,射杀他令海利伤透了心\N{\rEng}Broke Captain Hadley's heart to shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.86,1:39:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,事实如此\N{\rEng}Truly, it did.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.36,1:39:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只有忘掉这件事\N{\rEng}We just have to put it behind us.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.47,1:39:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,继续生活\N{\rEng}Move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.30,1:39:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,到此为止\N{\rEng}I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.11,1:39:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我不干了\N{\rEng}Everything stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.71,1:39:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你找别人帮你洗钱\N{\rEng}Get someone else to run your scams.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.31,1:39:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,不会停止\N{\rEng}Nothing stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.48,1:39:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,要继续\N{\rEng}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.06,1:39:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,否则我要你生不如死\N{\rEng}Or you will do the hardest time there is.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.56,1:39:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,不再让警卫保护你\N{\rEng}No more protection from the guards.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.09,1:39:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,不再让你一人一间牢房  把你丢到鸡奸狂当中\N{\rEng}I'll pull you out of that 1 -bunk Hilton and cast you down with the sodomites.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.40,1:39:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,日日夜夜轮奸不休\N{\rEng}You'll think you've been fucked by a train.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.24,1:39:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,图书馆呢\N{\rEng}And the library?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.41,1:39:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,没了\N{\rEng}Gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.01,1:39:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,用砖头封死掉\N{\rEng}Sealed off, brick by brick.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.04,1:39:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,在操场焚书\N{\rEng}We'll have us a little book barbecue in the yard.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.91,1:39:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,几里外都看得见火光\N{\rEng}They'll see the flames for miles.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.25,1:39:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,大家围着火跳红蕃舞\N{\rEng}We'll dance around it like wild Injuns.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.35,1:40:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我的话你懂吗\N{\rEng}You understand me? Catching my drift?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.09,1:40:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我是呆瓜吗\N{\rEng}Or am I being obtuse?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.74,1:40:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,再关他一个月考虑\N{\rEng}Give him another month to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.12,1:41:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,老婆说她很难了解我\N{\rEng}My wife used to say I'm a hard man to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.99,1:41:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,像一本合起来的书\N{\rEng}Like a closed book.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.63,1:41:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,她整天这样抱怨\N{\rEng}Complained about it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.60,1:41:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,她很漂亮\N{\rEng}She was beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.57,1:41:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我多么爱她呀\N{\rEng}God, I loved her.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.81,1:41:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是不擅表达\N{\rEng}I didn't know how to show it, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.78,1:41:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,是我杀了她\N{\rEng}I killed her, Red.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.32,1:41:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,枪不是我开的\N{\rEng}I didn't pull the trigger
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.55,1:41:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,但我害她离我远去\N{\rEng}but I drove her away.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.79,1:41:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,是我的脾气害她的\N{\rEng}That's why she died, because of me
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.69,1:41:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,害死了她\N{\rEng}the way I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.07,1:41:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但你不是杀人犯\N{\rEng}That don't make you a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.28,1:42:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,也许不算是好丈夫\N{\rEng}Bad husband, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.68,1:42:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,可以后悔  但你无罪\N{\rEng}Feel bad about it if you want,but you didn't pull the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.15,1:42:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rEng}No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.89,1:42:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,是别人干的没错\N{\rEng}Somebody else did.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.06,1:42:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但却由我受罚\N{\rEng}And I wound up in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.63,1:42:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,大概是我命薄\N{\rEng}Bad luck, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.08,1:42:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,谁都可能\N{\rEng}It floats around.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.90,1:42:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,沾染霉运\N{\rEng}It's got to land on somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.04,1:42:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,刚好轮到我\N{\rEng}It was my turn, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.64,1:42:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我被卷入龙卷风\N{\rEng}I was in the path of the tornado.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.35,1:42:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,只是没想到刮了这么久\N{\rEng}I just didn't expect the storm would last as long as it has.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.66,1:42:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你有可能假释吗\N{\rEng}Think you'll ever get out of here?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.60,1:42:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我\N{\rEng}Me?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.60,1:43:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,有呀\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.94,1:43:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,要等我老得神智不清才行\N{\rEng}One day, when I got a long, white beard
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.44,1:43:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我出狱后有地方去\N{\rEng}and two or three marbles rolling around upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.64,1:43:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我跟你说我要去哪儿\N{\rEng}I tell you where I'd go.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.75,1:43:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,芝华塔尼欧\N{\rEng}Zihuatanejo.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.28,1:43:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rEng}Say what?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.78,1:43:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,芝华塔尼欧\N{\rEng}Zihuatanejo.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.55,1:43:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,在墨西哥\N{\rEng}It's in Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.59,1:43:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,太平洋边的小地方\N{\rEng}A little place on the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.86,1:43:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-知道墨西哥人怎样说太平洋的吗   -不知道\N{\rEng}-You know what the Mexicans say about the Pacific? -No
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.46,1:43:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,那是没有回忆的海洋\N{\rEng}They say it has no memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.43,1:43:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我要在那儿度此余生\N{\rEng}That's where I want to live the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.74,1:43:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,没有回忆的温暖地\N{\rEng}A warm place with no memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.48,1:43:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,在海边\N{\rEng}Open up a little hotel
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.12,1:43:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,开个小旅馆\N{\rEng}right on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.22,1:43:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,买条破船\N{\rEng}Buy some worthless old boat
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.95,1:43:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,整修一新\N{\rEng}and fix it up new.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.32,1:43:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,载客出海\N{\rEng}Take my guests out
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.39,1:44:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,包船海钓\N{\rEng}charter fishing.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.60,1:44:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,芝华塔尼欧\N{\rEng}Zihuatanejo.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.87,1:44:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你在那地方也大有可为\N{\rEng}In a place like that, I could use a man that knows how to get things.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.28,1:44:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我在外头吃不开的\N{\rEng}I don't think I could make it on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.79,1:44:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我一生都耗在肖申克\N{\rEng}I been in here most of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.29,1:44:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经体制化了\N{\rEng}I'm an institutional man now.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.96,1:44:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,就像老布\N{\rEng}Just like Brooks was.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.17,1:44:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你别小看自己\N{\rEng}You underestimate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.44,1:44:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我不这么认为\N{\rEng}I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.87,1:44:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我在牢里让你有求必应\N{\rEng}In here I'm the guy who can get things for you, sure, but
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.58,1:44:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,一出社会电话簿里样样有\N{\rEng}outside all you need is the Yellow Pages.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.31,1:44:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,但我连查都不会查\N{\rEng}Hell, I wouldn't know where to begin.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.69,1:45:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,太平洋\N{\rEng}Pacific Ocean?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.72,1:45:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,狗屁\N{\rEng}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.32,1:45:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,大的我心都毛了\N{\rEng}Scare me to death, something that big.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.72,1:45:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会\N{\rEng}Not me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.23,1:45:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,老婆和她情夫不是我杀的\N{\rEng}I didn't shoot my wife,and I didn't shoot her lover.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.73,1:45:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我犯的错已偿清\N{\rEng}Whatever mistakes I made,I've paid for them and then some.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.00,1:45:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,一间旅店  一叶扁舟\N{\rEng}That hotel, that boat
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.27,1:45:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,这种要求并不过分\N{\rEng}I don't think that's too much to ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.41,1:45:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你不该有此妄想\N{\rEng}You shouldn't be doing this to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.05,1:45:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,完全痴人说梦\N{\rEng}This is just shitty pipe dreams.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.52,1:45:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,墨西哥和这儿可以说是\N{\rEng}Mexico is way down there and you're in here
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.19,1:45:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,天南地北\N{\rEng}and that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.09,1:45:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,话是没错\N{\rEng}Yeah, right.That's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.43,1:45:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,远在天涯海角\N{\rEng}It's down there and I'm in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.40,1:45:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,反正人只要二选一\N{\rEng}I guess it comes down to a simple choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.04,1:45:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,忙着活\N{\rEng}Get busy living
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.91,1:45:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,或忙着死\N{\rEng}or get busy dying.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.51,1:46:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪\N{\rEng}Andy
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.52,1:46:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞德\N{\rEng}Red
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.05,1:46:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,等你假释后  帮我个忙\N{\rEng}If you ever get out of here,do me a favor.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.99,1:46:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,没问题  你说\N{\rEng}Sure, Andy. Anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.13,1:46:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在巴克斯顿有个大干田  知道巴克斯顿吗\N{\rEng}There's a big hayfield up near Buxton.You know where Buxton is?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.47,1:46:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,-那一带田多得很  -有一处与众不同\N{\rEng}-A lot of hayfields up there. -One in particular.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.80,1:46:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,它有长石墙  北端有大橡树\N{\rEng}It's got a long rock wall with a big oak tree at the north end.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.94,1:46:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,美得像福斯特的诗\N{\rEng}It's like something out of a Robert Frost poem.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.75,1:46:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我在那儿向她求婚\N{\rEng}It's where I asked my wife to marry me.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.65,1:46:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我们去野餐\N{\rEng}We went there for a picnic
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.15,1:46:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在橡树下交合\N{\rEng}and made love under that oak
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.92,1:46:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我开口  她首肯\N{\rEng}and I asked and she said yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.16,1:46:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,答应我  瑞德\N{\rEng}Promise me, Red.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.83,1:46:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你终于假释了\N{\rEng}If you ever get out
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.67,1:46:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,去找到那个地方\N{\rEng}find that spot.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.33,1:46:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,在石墙底有一颗奇怪的石头\N{\rEng}At the base of that wall, there's a rock that has no earthly business in Maine.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.31,1:47:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,黑色的火山玻璃\N{\rEng}Piece of black, volcanic glass.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.01,1:47:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,底下埋着东西给你\N{\rEng}Something's buried under it I want you to have.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.45,1:47:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rEng}What, Andy?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.12,1:47:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你埋着什么\N{\rEng}What's buried under there?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.45,1:47:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你搬开它\N{\rEng}You'll have to pry it up
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.52,1:47:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,就知道\N{\rEng}to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.70,1:47:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你们听我说\N{\rEng}No, I'm telling you. The guy is
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.30,1:47:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,他胡言乱语\N{\rEng}He's talking funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.14,1:47:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我真担心他\N{\rEng}I'm really worried about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.24,1:47:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要盯紧他\N{\rEng}Let's keep an eye on him.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.87,1:47:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,白天不要紧  晚上孤伶伶的\N{\rEng}That's fine during the day,but at night he's all alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.58,1:47:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,天哪\N{\rEng}Oh, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.05,1:47:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.38,1:47:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪今天到载货区\N{\rEng}Andy come down to the loading dock today.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.35,1:47:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,向我要一条绳子\N{\rEng}He asked me for a length of rope.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.65,1:47:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,-绳子   -六尺长\N{\rEng}-Rope? -Six feet long.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.59,1:47:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你给了他\N{\rEng}And you gave it to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.83,1:47:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我凭什么不给\N{\rEng}Sure. Why wouldn't I?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.83,1:47:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-天  赫伍呀  -怎么想的到\N{\rEng}-Jesus! Heywood. -How was I supposed to know?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.17,1:48:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你忘了老布\N{\rEng}Remember Brooks Hatlen?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.90,1:48:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,不  安迪不会寻短\N{\rEng}Andy would never do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.27,1:48:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,绝对不会\N{\rEng}Never.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.41,1:48:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,谁知道呢\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.58,1:48:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,人的忍耐是有限度的\N{\rEng}Every man has his breaking point.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.95,1:48:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,动作快  我要回家\N{\rEng}Lickety-split.Want to get home.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.52,1:48:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,马上好了\N{\rEng}Just about finished, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.41,1:48:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚22要存三笔\N{\rEng}Three deposits tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.00,1:48:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,把衣物送洗\N{\rEng}Get my stuff down to the laundry.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.12,1:48:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,还有鞋子要\N{\rEng}And shine my shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.95,1:48:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,-擦的雪亮  -是的\N{\rEng}-I want them looking like mirrors. -Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.39,1:49:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你回来真好  安迪\N{\rEng}It's good having you back.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.80,1:49:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,没有你差多了\N{\rEng}Place wasn't the same without you.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.54,1:49:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,熄灯\N{\rEng}Lights out!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.45,1:50:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我也曾熬过孤寂长夜\N{\rEng}I've had some long nights in stir.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.52,1:50:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,独自在内心东想西想\N{\rEng}Alone in the dark with nothing but your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.38,1:50:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,时间慢的如同刀割\N{\rEng}time can draw out like a blade.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.39,1:50:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我毕生最长的一夜\N{\rEng}That was the longest night of my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.24,1:50:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,回报\N{\rEng}Give me a count!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.92,1:51:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,-三南层到齐  -收到\N{\rEng}-Tier 3 south, -clear!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.89,1:51:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,二层245房没人\N{\rEng}Man missing on tier 2, cell 245!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:13.26,1:51:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,杜弗伦\N{\rEng}Dufresne!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.86,1:51:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,别让大家等你\N{\rEng}Come out. You're holding up the show!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.43,1:51:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,别让大家等你  等我找上来你就没命\N{\rEng}Don't make me come down or I'll thump your skull for you!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.41,1:51:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我还得等你一个  你敢耽搁我时间\N{\rEng}Damn it, you're putting me behind!I got a schedule to keep.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.45,1:51:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,你若没死没病  就倒霉了\N{\rEng}You'd better be sick or dead in there.I shit you not!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.95,1:51:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,听见没有\N{\rEng}You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.39,1:51:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我的老天爷\N{\rEng}Oh, my Holy God.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.48,1:52:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这一区每人都要问\N{\rEng}I want every man on this cellblock questioned.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.48,1:52:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,-先从他朋友开始  -谁\N{\rEng}-Start with that friend of his. -Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.22,1:52:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,他\N{\rEng}him
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.62,1:52:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,打开237房\N{\rEng}Open 237.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.69,1:52:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,什么叫做他不见了   这算什么鬼话\N{\rEng}What do you mean, "He just wasn't here"? Don't say that to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.23,1:52:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你再说就试试看\N{\rEng}Don't tell me that again.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.76,1:52:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,但他真的不见了\N{\rEng}But sir, he wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.03,1:52:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道  我没眼睛吗\N{\rEng}I can see that, Haig!Think I'm blind?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.17,1:52:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你说我\N{\rEng}Is that what you're saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.77,1:52:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,-没长眼睛吗   -不敢  长官\N{\rEng}-Am I blind, Haig? -No, sir!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.34,1:52:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你呢   你没长眼睛吗\N{\rEng}What about you. You blind?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.34,1:52:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,-你说这是什么   -昨晚的点名单\N{\rEng}-Tell me what this is. -Last night's count.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.11,1:52:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,上面明明写着杜弗伦\N{\rEng}You see Dufresne's name there?I sure do. Right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.62,1:52:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,"杜弗伦"\N{\rEng}"Dufresne."
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.62,1:52:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,熄灯时\N{\rEng}He was in his cell
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.32,1:52:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他在房里\N{\rEng}at lights out.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:50.52,1:52:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,早上也应该在才对\N{\rEng}Reasonable he'd be here in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.79,1:52:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,把他找到\N{\rEng}I want him found.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.63,1:52:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,一刻都不能拖  现在找\N{\rEng}Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.33,1:53:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.53,1:53:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,搜人去  快点\N{\rEng}Let's go. Move your butts.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.21,1:53:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,站住\N{\rEng}Stand.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.64,1:53:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,你说\N{\rEng}Well?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.15,1:53:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,说什么\N{\rEng}Well, what?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.35,1:53:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你们俩成天粘在一起\N{\rEng}I see you two all the time.You're thick as thieves, you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.89,1:53:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他一定说过什么\N{\rEng}He must have said something.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.12,1:53:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,报告典狱长\N{\rEng}No, sir, Warden.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.99,1:53:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rEng}Not a word.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.83,1:53:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,那真是奇迹了\N{\rEng}Lord, it's a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.00,1:53:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,人像屁一般凭空消失\N{\rEng}Man vanished like a fart in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.23,1:53:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,不见踪影\N{\rEng}Nothing left
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.23,1:53:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,只剩一堆石头\N{\rEng}but some damn rocks on a windowsill.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.17,1:53:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,还有墙上那骚货\N{\rEng}And that cupcake on the wall.Let's ask her.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.11,1:53:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,问她吧  也许她知道\N{\rEng}Maybe she knows.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.11,1:53:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你说呀  短裤妞儿\N{\rEng}What say there, fuzzy-britches?Feel like talking?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:47.28,1:53:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,她不会说的\N{\rEng}Guess not.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.15,1:53:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,别人不说  为何她要说\N{\rEng}Why should she be any different?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:52.42,1:53:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  你们有预谋\N{\rEng}This is a conspiracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.72,1:53:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这样\N{\rEng}That's what this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.16,1:54:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,一个超级大阴谋\N{\rEng}One big, damn conspiracy!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.16,1:54:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都有份\N{\rEng}And everyone's in on it!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.80,1:54:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,包括她\N{\rEng}Including her!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.00,1:54:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,1966年\N{\rEng}In 1966
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.90,1:54:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪·杜弗伦逃离\N{\rEng}Andy Dufresne escaped
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.50,1:54:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,肖申克监狱\N{\rEng}from Shawshank Prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:48.31,1:54:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,狱方只寻获泥囚衣\N{\rEng}All they found was a muddy set of prison clothes
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.51,1:54:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,一块肥皂\N{\rEng}a bar of soap
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.25,1:54:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,一把石锤\N{\rEng}and an old rock hammer
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.01,1:54:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,一把几乎解体的石锤\N{\rEng}damn near worn down to the nub.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:01.99,1:55:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾夸口要花六百年才挖的通的隧道\N{\rEng}I had thought it'd take a man 600 years to tunnel through the wall with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.39,1:55:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪花了不到20年\N{\rEng}Old Andy did it in less than 20.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.31,1:55:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他喜爱研究地质\N{\rEng}Oh, Andy loved geology.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.38,1:55:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,碎石令他想一探究竟\N{\rEng}I imagine it appealed to his meticulous nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.95,1:55:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,刑期如同\N{\rEng}An ice age here
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.22,1:55:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,冰河时代\N{\rEng}million years of mountain building there.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.73,1:55:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,地质学探讨压力及时间\N{\rEng}Geology is the study of pressure and time.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.40,1:55:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是凿通的关键\N{\rEng}That's all it takes, really.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.13,1:55:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,压力\N{\rEng}Pressure
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.87,1:55:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,和时间\N{\rEng}and time.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.47,1:55:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,和一张够大的海报\N{\rEng}That and a big goddamn poster.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.34,1:55:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,就我说的\N{\rEng}Like I said
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.01,1:56:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在牢里  没事也得找事做\N{\rEng}in prison, a man will do anything to keep his mind occupied.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:05.82,1:56:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,原来安迪的最大的嗜好\N{\rEng}Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting his wall out into the exercise yard
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.16,1:56:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,就是一点一滴倾倒废土\N{\rEng}a handful at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:14.39,1:56:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,大概就在汤米死后\N{\rEng}I guess after Tommy was killed
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.66,1:56:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪决定不再久留\N{\rEng}Andy decided he'd been here long enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.83,1:56:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,动作快  我要回家\N{\rEng}Lickety-split.I want to get home.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.14,1:56:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,马上就好了\N{\rEng}I'm just about finished, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.63,1:56:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚要存三笔\N{\rEng}Three deposits tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.87,1:56:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪遵命行事\N{\rEng}Andy did like he was told.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.37,1:57:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,把鞋子擦的雪亮\N{\rEng}Buffed those shoes to a high mirror-shine.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.55,1:57:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,警卫都没注意\N{\rEng}The guards simply didn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.15,1:57:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我也没有\N{\rEng}Neither did I.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:09.82,1:57:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,说真的\N{\rEng}I mean, seriously
Dialogue: 0,1:57:11.55,1:57:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,谁会注意别人的鞋子\N{\rEng}how often do you really look at a man's shoes?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:18.11,1:59:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪就这样爬向自由\N{\rEng}Andy crawled to freedom through 500 yards
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.51,1:59:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,在恶臭中匍匐五百码\N{\rEng}of shit-smelling foulness I can't even imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:25.85,1:59:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,要我爬才不干\N{\rEng}Or maybe I just don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:32.59,1:59:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,五百码\N{\rEng}Five hundred yards.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:35.46,1:59:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,五座橄榄球场宽\N{\rEng}That's the length of five football fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.17,1:59:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,几乎长达半里\N{\rEng}Just shy of half a mile.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:36.96,2:00:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,次日清晨  在拉寇儿坦露她的秘密之时\N{\rEng}The next morning, right about the time Raquel was spilling her secret
Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.86,2:00:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,一个从未现世的人\N{\rEng}a man nobody ever laid eyes on before
Dialogue: 0,2:00:44.93,2:00:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,走进缅因国家银行\N{\rEng}strolled into the Maine National Bank.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:48.10,2:00:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,在那之前  他不是实体\N{\rEng}Until that moment, he didn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:51.84,2:00:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-只存在于文件上  -有何干贵\N{\rEng}-Except on paper. -May I help you?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:54.61,2:00:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他各种证件都有\N{\rEng}He had all the proper ID
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.74,2:01:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,驾照  出生证  社会保险卡\N{\rEng}driver's license, birth certificate,Social Security card
Dialogue: 0,2:01:00.88,2:01:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,签名分毫不差\N{\rEng}And the signature was a spot-on match.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:03.62,2:01:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,失去您的生意令我真心遗憾\N{\rEng}I must say I'm sorry to be losing your business.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:06.92,2:01:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,祝您侨居愉快\N{\rEng}I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:09.46,2:01:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:11.22,2:01:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,一定的\N{\rEng}I'm sure I will.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:13.29,2:01:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这是银行本票  就这样吗\N{\rEng}Here's your cashier's check, sir.Will there be anything else?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:16.83,2:01:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,麻烦你\N{\rEng}Please.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:18.40,2:01:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,帮我寄出去好吗\N{\rEng}Would you add this to your outgoing mail?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:21.40,2:01:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,乐意之至\N{\rEng}I'd be happy to.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:24.40,2:01:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-再会  -保重\N{\rEng}-Good day, sir. -Good day.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:26.67,2:01:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,史蒂文斯造访十几家银行\N{\rEng}Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks in the Portland area that morning.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:31.58,2:01:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,总共加起来\N{\rEng}All told, he blew town
Dialogue: 0,2:01:33.38,2:01:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他领走诺顿37万元\N{\rEng}with better than $370,000 of Warden Norton's money.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:38.92,2:01:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,19年的遣散费\N{\rEng}Severance pay for 19 years.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:48.93,2:01:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,早安  波特兰号角日报\N{\rEng}Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:51.13,2:01:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}肖申克监狱  贪污谋杀
Dialogue: 0,2:02:01.74,2:02:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}主的审判迅速降临
Dialogue: 0,2:02:20.26,2:02:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}亲爱的典狱长  你说的对\N得救之道  就在其中
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.98,2:02:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你是海利   你有权保持缄默\N{\rEng}Byron Hadley? You have the right to remain silent.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:47.19,2:02:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,若你放弃这权利  你的话将成为呈堂证供\N{\rEng}If you give up this right, anything you say can be held against you in court.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:52.06,2:02:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我没在场目睹  听说\N{\rEng}I wasn't there to see, but I hear Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl
Dialogue: 0,2:02:56.73,2:02:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,海利哭成泪人儿\N{\rEng}when they took him away.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:04.10,2:03:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,诺顿无意乖乖就范\N{\rEng}Norton had no intention of going that quietly.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:23.46,2:03:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,诺顿\N{\rEng}Samuel Norton.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:24.99,2:03:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,诺顿  我们有拘票  开门\N{\rEng}We have a warrant for your arrest. Open up.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:30.86,2:03:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,把门打开\N{\rEng}Open the door.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:33.80,2:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我不清楚哪一把\N{\rEng}I'm not sure which key.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:44.74,2:03:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,别自找麻烦\N{\rEng}Make it easy on yourself, Norton!
Dialogue: 0,2:03:58.66,2:04:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我猜他脑中最后一件事\N{\rEng}I like to think the last thing that went through his head
Dialogue: 0,2:04:02.33,2:04:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,除了枪子儿\N{\rEng}other than that bullet
Dialogue: 0,2:04:04.13,2:04:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,就是在想安迪为何能扳倒他\N{\rEng}was to wonder how the hell Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:11.07,2:04:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,典狱长见阎王之后不久\N{\rEng}Not long after the warden deprived us of his company
Dialogue: 0,2:04:14.81,2:04:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我收到一张明信片\N{\rEng}I got a postcard in the mail.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:18.34,2:04:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,没写字  但有邮戳\N{\rEng}It was blank,but the postmark said
Dialogue: 0,2:04:21.38,2:04:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,来自德州汉考克堡\N{\rEng}Fort Hancock, Texas.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:24.05,2:04:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,汉考克堡\N{\rEng}Fort Hancock
Dialogue: 0,2:04:25.68,2:04:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,在边界上\N{\rEng}right on the border.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:27.82,2:04:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪已离开美国\N{\rEng}That's where Andy crossed.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:30.39,2:04:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,驾着敞蓬车奔向南方\N{\rEng}When I picture him heading south in his own car with the top down
Dialogue: 0,2:04:34.86,2:04:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,想到这画面就令我开怀\N{\rEng}it always makes me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:38.93,2:04:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪\N{\rEng}Andy Dufresne
Dialogue: 0,2:04:40.87,2:04:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,他涉过肮脏污河\N{\rEng}who crawled through a river of shit
Dialogue: 0,2:04:43.10,2:04:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,涤尽罪恶  在彼岸重生\N{\rEng}and came out clean on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:46.34,2:04:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪·杜弗伦\N{\rEng}Andy Dufresne
Dialogue: 0,2:04:48.51,2:04:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,太平洋在望\N{\rEng}headed for the Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:53.08,2:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,海利掐住他说\N{\rEng}Hadley's got him by the throat, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:55.45,2:04:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"他活的不耐烦了"\N{\rEng}He says, "I believe this boy's about to have himself an accident."
Dialogue: 0,2:04:59.45,2:05:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,老友们常聊起他\N{\rEng}Those of us who knew him best talk about him often.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:02.99,2:05:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他那些惊人之举\N{\rEng}I swear, the stuff he pulled
Dialogue: 0,2:05:04.89,2:05:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"请我朋友喝啤酒吧"\N{\rEng}"My friends could use a couple of beers."
Dialogue: 0,2:05:08.19,2:05:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,真的做到了\N{\rEng}And he got it!
Dialogue: 0,2:05:11.10,2:05:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他走了  有时\N{\rEng}Sometimes it makes me sad, though
Dialogue: 0,2:05:13.77,2:05:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,令我感伤\N{\rEng}Andy being gone.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:15.90,2:05:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,有的鸟毕竟是关不住的\N{\rEng}I have to remind myself that some birds aren't meant to be caged.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.51,2:05:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他们的羽翼太光辉了\N{\rEng}Their feathers are just too bright.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:24.28,2:05:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们飞走\N{\rEng}And when they fly away
Dialogue: 0,2:05:26.45,2:05:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你会由衷庆贺他获得自由\N{\rEng}the part of you that knows it was a sin to lock them up does rejoice.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:31.92,2:05:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,无奈的是\N{\rEng}But still
Dialogue: 0,2:05:33.65,2:05:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你得继续在这乏味之地苟活\N{\rEng}the place you live in is that much more drab and empty that they're gone.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:42.18,2:05:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我真怀念这位友伴\N{\rEng}I guess I just miss my friend.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:09.02,2:06:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,请坐\N{\rEng}Please sit down.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:16.03,2:06:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,阿里斯·瑞丁\N{\rEng}Ellis Boyd Redding
Dialogue: 0,2:06:18.13,2:06:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你判无期徒刑  已关40年\N{\rEng}your files say you've served 40 years of a life sentence.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:22.20,2:06:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你改过自新了吗\N{\rEng}You feel you've been rehabilitated?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:26.21,2:06:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,改过自新\N{\rEng}Rehabilitated?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:29.81,2:06:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,要让我说\N{\rEng}Well, now, let me see.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:32.71,2:06:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我根本不懂那是什么\N{\rEng}I don't have any idea what that means.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:37.15,2:06:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,就是重返社会\N{\rEng}It means you're ready to rejoin society
Dialogue: 0,2:06:39.99,2:06:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这我懂  年轻人\N{\rEng}I know what you think it means, sonny.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:44.49,2:06:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,它对我只是虚词\N{\rEng}To me it's just a made-up word.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:47.83,2:06:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,政客发明的词\N{\rEng}A politician's word so that
Dialogue: 0,2:06:50.60,2:06:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,使你们穿西装打领带的\N{\rEng}young fellas like yourself can wear a suit and a tie
Dialogue: 0,2:06:54.60,2:06:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,有活干\N{\rEng}and have a job.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:58.17,2:07:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,你到底想了解什么\N{\rEng}What do you really want to know?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:01.04,2:07:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我后悔犯罪吗\N{\rEng}Am I sorry for what I did?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:03.44,2:07:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你后悔吗\N{\rEng}Well, are you?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:06.51,2:07:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有一天不后悔\N{\rEng}There's not a day goes by I don't feel regret.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:10.72,2:07:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但并非只有受过惩罚才后悔\N{\rEng}Not because I'm in here or because you think I should.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:17.65,2:07:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我回首前尘往事\N{\rEng}I look back on the way I was then
Dialogue: 0,2:07:22.36,2:07:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,那个\N{\rEng}a young
Dialogue: 0,2:07:24.63,2:07:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,犯下重罪的孩子\N{\rEng}stupid kid who committed that terrible crime.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:31.14,2:07:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我想跟他沟通\N{\rEng}I want to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:34.77,2:07:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我试图讲道理\N{\rEng}I want to try and talk some sense to him.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:37.98,2:07:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,让他明了\N{\rEng}Tell him the way things are.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:42.01,2:07:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,但我办不到\N{\rEng}But I can't.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:45.65,2:07:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,那个少年早就不见了\N{\rEng}That kid's long gone
Dialogue: 0,2:07:48.85,2:07:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,只剩下我的垂老之躯\N{\rEng}and this old man is all that's left.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:53.03,2:07:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我得接受事实\N{\rEng}I got to live with that.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:55.86,2:07:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,改过自新\N{\rEng}Rehabilitated?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:57.93,2:07:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,狗屁不通的词\N{\rEng}It's just a bullshit word.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:00.70,2:08:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你盖章吧  别浪费我的时间\N{\rEng}So you go on and stamp your forms,sonny, and stop wasting my time.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:06.71,2:08:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉你一句实话\N{\rEng}Because to tell you the truth
Dialogue: 0,2:08:09.31,2:08:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我他妈的不在乎\N{\rEng}I don't give a shit.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:23.95,2:08:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}核准
Dialogue: 0,2:09:20.28,2:09:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}老布到此一游
Dialogue: 0,2:09:37.83,2:09:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\rEng}Here you go, miss.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:42.17,2:09:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,可以上厕所吗\N{\rEng}Restroom break?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:49.01,2:09:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,别要尿尿就来报告  要去就去  懂吗\N{\rEng}You don't need to ask me every time you need to go take a piss. Just go.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:54.58,2:09:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rEng}yes
Dialogue: 0,2:10:06.59,2:10:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我报告了40年\N{\rEng}Forty years I've been asking permission to piss.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:10.50,2:10:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,没报告  一滴也挤不出\N{\rEng}I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:17.00,2:10:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我得面对残酷的事实\N{\rEng}There's a harsh truth to face.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:20.84,2:10:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我根本混不下去\N{\rEng}No way I'm going to make it on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:31.62,2:10:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我一心想违反假释\N{\rEng}All I do anymore is think of ways to break my parole
Dialogue: 0,2:10:36.12,2:10:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,也许能重返肖申克\N{\rEng}so maybe they'd send me back.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:43.80,2:10:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,活在恐惧中真是糟糕\N{\rEng}Terrible thing, to live in fear.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:47.13,2:10:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,老布体会过\N{\rEng}Brooks Hatlen knew it.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:49.00,2:10:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他看透了\N{\rEng}Knew it all too well.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:52.54,2:10:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我只想回到有意义的地方\N{\rEng}All I want is to be back where things make sense.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:56.38,2:10:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,不必整天担惊受怕\N{\rEng}Where I won't have to be afraid all the time.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:01.11,2:11:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,只有一件事阻止了我\N{\rEng}Only one thing stops me.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:04.92,2:11:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我向安迪做的承诺\N{\rEng}A promise I made to Andy.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:27.84,2:11:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,到了\N{\rEng}There it is.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:39.58,2:11:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢您\N{\rEng}Much obliged, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:49.95,2:11:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}巴克斯顿
Dialogue: 0,2:15:20.57,2:15:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,亲爱的瑞德\N{\rEng}Dear Red:
Dialogue: 0,2:15:22.07,2:15:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你读到信就代表出狱了\N{\rEng}If you're reading this,you've gotten out
Dialogue: 0,2:15:24.74,2:15:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,跑了这么远  再坚持一下吧\N{\rEng}and if you've come this far,maybe you'd come a bit further.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:29.08,2:15:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,还记得地名吗\N{\rEng}You remember the name of the town, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:33.85,2:15:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,芝华塔尼欧\N{\rEng}Zihuatanejo.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:36.99,2:15:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你能帮我实现计划\N{\rEng}I could use a good man to help me get my project on wheels.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:41.09,2:15:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我备妥棋盘等着你\N{\rEng}I'll keep an eye out for you,and the chessboard ready.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:45.43,2:15:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,记住\N{\rEng}Remember, Red
Dialogue: 0,2:15:47.17,2:15:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,希望是好事\N{\rEng}hope is a good thing
Dialogue: 0,2:15:49.47,2:15:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,也许是人间至善\N{\rEng}maybe the best of things.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:51.67,2:15:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,而美好的事永不消逝\N{\rEng}And no good thing ever dies.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:54.37,2:15:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,希望你读到信时\N{\rEng}I will be hoping that this letter finds you
Dialogue: 0,2:15:57.44,2:15:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,尚且健康\N{\rEng}and finds you well.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:59.68,2:16:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你的朋友\N{\rEng}Your friend
Dialogue: 0,2:16:01.11,2:16:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,安迪\N{\rEng}Andy.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:36.11,2:16:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"忙着活\N{\rEng}"Get busy living
Dialogue: 0,2:16:38.05,2:16:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,或忙着死"\N{\rEng}or get busy dying."
Dialogue: 0,2:16:42.65,2:16:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,真有道理\N{\rEng}That's goddamn right.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:47.09,2:16:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs16\b1}老布到此一游\N瑞德也来过
Dialogue: 0,2:16:50.06,2:16:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,这是生平第二次\N{\rEng}For the second time in my life
Dialogue: 0,2:16:52.43,2:16:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我又犯了罪\N{\rEng}I'm guilty of committing a crime.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:56.07,2:16:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,违反假释出城\N{\rEng}Parole violation.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:58.67,2:17:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我怀疑警方会设路障逮我\N{\rEng}Of course I doubt they'll toss up any roadblocks for that.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:03.01,2:17:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我这种老贼可以免了\N{\rEng}Not for an old crook like me.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:05.24,2:17:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,德州汉考克堡\N{\rEng}Fort Hancock, Texas, please.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:10.95,2:17:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我激动地坐不住  不停地想\N{\rEng}I find I'm so excited I can barely sit still or hold a thought in my head.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:16.12,2:17:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,自由人才会这么兴奋吧\N{\rEng}I think it's the excitement only a free man can feel.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:19.66,2:17:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,踏上未知旅程的\N{\rEng}A free man at the start of a long journey
Dialogue: 0,2:17:22.36,2:17:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,自由人\N{\rEng}whose conclusion is uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:27.97,2:17:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望成功越过边界\N{\rEng}I hope I can make it across the border.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:32.14,2:17:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望能跟老友握握手\N{\rEng}I hope to see my friend and shake his hand.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:37.04,2:17:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望太平洋如梦中一般蓝\N{\rEng}I hope the Pacific is as blue as it has been in my dreams.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:42.95,2:17:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望\N{\rEng}I hope.
